title: aunt mary's bean casserole
directions: Drain juice from all the cans of beans, place in casserole dish.
Mix pepper, onion, salt, sugar and ketchup.
Pour over the beans.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes a good-size casserole, great for picnics.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: baked sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in baking dish.
Starting with sweet potatoes, place alternate layers of sliced potatoes and sliced apples in the baking dish.
Season each layer of apples with salt-cinnamon and sugars.
Over the top layer of apples, spread bread crumbs which have been mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: damn good chili*
directions: Heat cooker and brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients except kidney beans.
Close cover securely. Place pressure regulator on vent pipe.
Cook 5 minutes.
Let pressure drop of its own accord.
Add kidney beans and heat through.
Up to 2 cans of beans may be added.
Increase cayenne or chili powder for hotter chili.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with blender on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until top turns golden brown and pie "sets."

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt in small bowl.
Combine butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Mix with first mixture slowly by hand until well blended.
Add chips and nuts by hand.

title: tasty chicken and rice
directions: Cut meat in small pieces.
In a large skillet, brown meat for 8 minutes on medium heat.
Add Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 cup water, salt and bouillon cubes.
Add vegetables.
Put lid on skillet and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining water and soup mix.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and cover with lid.
Remove from heat and let stand.

title: grandma's pineapple salad
directions: Put dry Jell-O mix (from package) into medium-sized bowl or mold.
Add 1 cup boiling water to Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add cream cheese; mash with fork until cheese is in small pieces.
Add pineapple, 1/2 cup cold water and whipped cream.
Stir until well mixed.
Refrigerate for 4 to 6 hours, until firm.
Enjoy!

title: salmon oriental
directions: In a big skillet, heat oil and butter and quickly stir garlic in; do not brown.
Add the chicken broth and simmer the broccoli just until the broccoli is crisp-tender.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange in bowl by layers.
Let set several hours or overnight.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 1 1/2-inch slices and cook until tender. Chop
onion fine.
Chop bell pepper into small pieces.
Mix and salt to taste.
Marinate in Kraft dressing in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs until thoroughly incorporated.
In another bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients into sugar, oil and egg mixture, blending well.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Bake in a 15 x 10 x 2-inch greased pan at 300° for 1 hour.
Ice when cake has cooled.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Make out sausage into about 2-inch links.
Place sausage in microwave for about 3 minutes, until no longer pink and firm enough to roll up. Drain well.
Place about 1/2 slice cheese on each crescent triangle, then place sausage on top of cheese and roll up crescent roll, starting with long side.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and bake until brown.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Blend Lipton mix and sour cream.
Add cucumber, radishes and horseradish.
Chill.

title: lemon garlic broiled shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Saute garlic in butter until brown.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well. Pour mixture over shrimp.
Broil shrimp 4 inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes, basting once.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oriental dip
directions: In medium bowl combine all the ingredients except the assorted vegetables.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Stir before serving with vegetables.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pour into pan.
Bake 325° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage 'n apple salad
directions: Beat and chill several hours before serving.
Great with barbecued chicken.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Save broth.
Boil vegetables in water until tender.
Cut up chicken in casserole, drain vegetables and pour over chicken. Pour cream of chicken soup over vegetables.
Pour chicken broth on it.
Salt and pepper and stir.
Make biscuit dough.
Roll and cut in thin strips, put on top.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: hot orange cider punch
directions: Put in crock-pot, stirring well.
Cook on high for 2 to 3 hours.
This can be done on the stove.
Great in cold weather.
It also makes the house smell great!

title: baked lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray shallow baking dish with Pam. Add chicken, pouring lemon juice on each piece.
Sprinkle lemon pepper and garlic salt.
Spray chicken with Pam.
Bake 60 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill until served. Do not increase or lessen amounts called for.

title: mochiko chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Stir to mix well and marinate overnight. Fry in oil until brown.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Combine fruits and coconut in a bowl, then add sour cream and sugar to this mixture.
Mix carefully.
Chill.

title: banana split pie
directions: Crumble wafers for crust.
Layer sugar, pineapple, banana and Cool Whip, ending up with Cool Whip on the top.
Cool for 1 hour; serve.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add sugar, dates, eggs, salt and instant coffee.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Add vanilla and nuts; cook for 3 more minutes.
Carefully add cereal and 1 1/3 cups shredded coconut.
Mix thoroughly.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. Wet hands in cold water and form mixture into walnut size balls. Roll in remaining coconut.
Cool.

title: tortellini pasta salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Rinse with cold water.
Place tomatoes, finely chopped basil and parsley, garlic in a bowl.
Gently stir in remaining ingredients and gently stir together.
Add tortellini and toss to coat.
Can be refrigerated and served as a cold salad.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli until tender.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Mix
soup
and milk;
pour over broccoli.
Mix stuffing mix, water, margarine and egg; pour on top of soup and broccoli.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Melt caramels in water with margarine over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Combine sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Gradually add caramel mixture, mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grilled chicken sandwich
directions: Pour half of teriyaki sauce into a sealed container and add chicken.
Allow chicken to marinate for 1-2 hours, turning frequently.
Cut bread 1-1/2 inch thick slices.
Barbecue chicken until done, basting with remaining teriyaki sauce 2-3 times on each side.
Grill bread slices and pineapple rings lightly on both sides.
Place chicken on toasted bread, garnish with pineapple rings and serve hot.

title: polynesian-style skewered lamb and pineapple
directions: Combine lamb in plastic bag with dressing, soy and ginger. Marinate for 20 minutes at room temperature or all day in refrigerator.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Alternate chunks of lamb and pineapple on skewers (with fresh basil or mint leaves between, if desired).
Brush skewers lightly with reserved marinade.
Place skewers on broiler rack 2-inches from heat source.
Broil for 8 to 10 minutes per side.

title: make ahead cookie mix
directions: In very large bowl, combine butter, salt and baking powder. Using electric mixer, blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off (do not blend, scoop or sift flour). Add flour to butter mixture until blended and fine crumbs form, scraping the bowl often.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator for up to 4 weeks.

title: sugar-free syrup
directions: Cook apple juice and cornstarch until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat, stir in sweetener and flavorings.
Makes 1 cup.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Butter 12 x 8 x 2 pan, then add crackers and place asparagus on top.
Then add sliced eggs.
Add 1/2 cheese.
Pour cream of soup. Add rest of cheese.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple salad tropicale
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill until thickened and almost set.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: el porton's white cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese and put in saucepan.
Over medium-low heat, add just enough milk to melt the cheese to the desired consistency, stirring constantly so cheese doesn't burn.
Blend in finely chopped jalapenos to taste.

title: easy short ribs
directions: Turn oven to 250°.
Peel carrots and cut in half, lengthwise. Peel onions and cut in thick slices.
On about 3 thicknesses of heavy-duty foil, layer short ribs between vegetables and sprinkle onion soup mix over all. Seal tightly.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 3 to 4 hours. Turn oven off until ready to eat after 4 hours and never open the oven until done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni noodles; drain.
Mix with other ingredients. Chill.

title: spicy boiled crawfish
directions: In a very large boiler pot, combine 4 gallons of water with all ingredients except crawfish.
Bring to a boil and let boil for at least 20 minutes.
Add crawfish and cook for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and let set for 20 minutes to absorb seasonings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until crumbly.
Cook milk, sugar, cornstarch, flour, salt and egg yolks until thick. Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender; set aside. Combine next 5 ingredients and stir in broccoli.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs to cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in a large bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Spoon hot butter glaze over cake.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples with brown sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Place apple mixture in pie shell and dots of butter on top of apples.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple. Mix pudding with juice of pineapple. Mix with Cool Whip. Stir in pineapple; mix well. Stir in marshmallows, then stir in pecans. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: leftovers
directions: Saut green pepper and onion in margarine.
Add cheese and milk; stir until melted. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar; heat butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola until boiling (watch it).
Pour over flour and sugar mix, mixing well.
Add milk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Beat well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Ice while hot.

title: cool lemon pie
directions: Blend eggs and milk until smooth.
Add lemon juice gradually. Pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.
Freeze at least 1 hour.
Remove from freezer about 10 minutes before serving.
Slice and serve.
Garnish or not.

title: hunter style chicken
directions: Saute bacon in large skillet until partially cooked, then saute onion in same skillet until onion is tender.
Remove bacon and onion; set aside.
Drain drippings from skillet, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Brown chicken in remaining drippings, sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Drain excess fat.
Combine cooked bacon, onion, tomatoes, 57 sauce and sugar. Pour over chicken. Cover, simmer 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender, basting occasionally.
Thicken sauce with flour/water mixture, if desired. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: new orleans jambalaya
directions: In a 5-quart kettle, brown chicken in oil.
Take out and set aside.
Brown ham.
Stir in garlic and onions.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Return chicken to kettle.
Stir in tomatoes, salt, Tabasco sauce and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar.
Press evenly in 8 x 8 x 2-inch ungreased pan, building up 1/2-inch edges.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients (except powdered sugar) until fluffy.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake 25 minutes or until no indention when touched.
Cool and sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, melted margarine, milk and vanilla.
Do not clean beaters off after mixing.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together the flour, brown sugar, pecans and melted margarine.
Spread over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until topping has browned.

title: pear preserves
directions: Take 2 cups sugar and 2 cups water and boil 15 minutes, then add pears in and boil 15 minutes.
Add 2 cups sugar and 1 cup water and cook until done.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly. Leave skin on. Cut up potatoes either across, lengthwise or in chunks. Place in large bowl. Salt and pepper sparingly. Cut up onion and margarine over potatoes. Cover and cook in microwave for 3 minutes. Take out. Toss around in margarine. Return to microwave for another 3 minutes. Repeat until desired tenderness.

title: chocolate chip cookie
directions: Mix and set aside the flour, soda and salt.
Mix until creamy the butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
This is a good salad.

title: zesty chicken salad casserole
directions: Drain mushrooms and save liquid. Saute onion in butter; add salt, pepper and mushroom liquid. Blend in soup. Add milk slowly until mixture thickens. In a large bowl, combine rice, mushrooms and chicken. Add soup mixture and stir gently. Spread in casserole dish and top with cheeses and pimentos. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy ricotta cheesecake
directions: Prepare cake mix as on box.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and put aside.
Separately mix Ricotta, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Fold into cake mix and marble with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: beans and sausage
directions: Wash beans 2 or 3 times.
Place sausage in large skillet. Render fat from sausage.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
Add vegetables to sausage and saute until soft.
Transfer mixture to large stock or crock-pot.
Add 2 quarts of water and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 3 hours or all night.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Serve over rice.

title: white party crunch
directions: Place candy coating in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50% power) 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in cereal and remaining ingredients.
Spread on wax paper to cool; break into pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Brown ground meat; drain fat.

Add onions to ground meat and saute. Heat together cream of mushroom soup with ground meat. Add broccoli and Cheez Whiz; mix well. Place cooked rice in a long buttered casserole dish; pour mixture over. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Cook sweet potatoes and peel.
Slice into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cube orange and remove seeds.
Grind orange and add water, sugar and coloring.
Cook until syrupy.
Mix flour and melted butter.
Add to syrup with the rest of ingredients.
Blend well and pour
over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute butter and onion.
Add soup, sour cream and Cheez Whiz.
Stir until blended over low heat.
Add potatoes and keep on low heat until potatoes are well heated.
Pour into a 10 x 15-inch glass pan.
Crush 1 package Ritz crackers and brown in 1 stick of butter.
Put on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly in center.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Drain cherries; reserve syrup.
Combine syrup with sugar and cornstarch in chafing dish or electric skillet.
Bring to a boil. Cook, stirring, until smooth and clear.
Add cherries and orange peel.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour all but 1 tablespoon brandy over cherries.
Ignite the remaining 1 tablespoon brandy and pour over cherries.
When flames begin to die down stir gently and ladle over servings of vanilla ice cream.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper, salt, chili powder and garlic in skillet until beef is browned.
Stir in separate meat particles.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 30 minutes, until rice is tender.
Stir often.
Serves 4.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Blend in all ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour or more.

title: bacon-cheese muffins
directions: Sift
together	thoroughly
flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; make well in center.	Combine egg, milk and oil; add all at once
to dry mixture along with cheese and bacon.
Stir just until moistened.	Fill well greased muffin pans.	Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: shrimp, crab, lobster or tuna salad
directions: Place soup in double boiler; crumble cheese and stir into soup until creamed.
Add salt and gelatin dissolved in small amount of water; stir until completely dissolved.
Remove from heat; cool. Add all other ingredients and whatever cooked seafood you plan to use and pour into 9x13-inch pan.
If tuna is used, scald and drain well before adding to soup mixture.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix all filling ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into the pie shell.
Bake in the middle of the oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Garnish with whipped cream if desired.

title: lemony apple muffins
directions: In a large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar. Add apple; toss to coat and set aside. In a separate bowl, blend butter, lemon zest, eggs and milk. Gently stir into the flour mixture. Divide mixture equally among 12 greased muffin tins.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put yeast in one cup warm water to dissolve.
To other cup water, add sugar and shortening.
Add water with yeast and gradually add flour.
Let rise in warm place.
Turn out on floured board and knead.
Cut with glass or cutter into small rolls. Place in buttered pan to rise.
Cook at 350°.
Before rolls are completely done, brush tops with butter and let brown.
Makes approximately 36.

title: shrimp in spicy sauce
directions: Shell, devein, rinse and pat dry the shrimp or prawns. Lightly coat them in the cornflour and set aside.
Combine wine vinegar, salt, sugar and soy sauce.
Heat oil and stir-fry shrimp/prawns quickly for about 2 minutes.
Add the garlic, ginger and spring onions and stir-fry for a further minute, then add the vinegar mixture.
Mix well; stir until the sauce bubbles.
Serve very hot.

title: worcestershire roast
directions: Add all ingredients to roast.
Cook at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: garlic tomato bruschetta
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Shake well. Add tomatoes and cheese. Toss gently. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Bring to room temperature to serve. Cut bread into 24 slices. Toast. Top with tomato mixture.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until almost tender.
Saute onion and green pepper in small amount of oil.
Add remaining ingredients; heat and pour over carrots.
Mix carefully. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: coconut igloos
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add pineapple, raisins and pecans. Spread this filling between 3 cookies.
Let stand at room temperature at least 8 hours.
Frost top and sides of igloos with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Serves 24.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add orange oil.
Stir in the dry ingredients.
Divide dough in half; wrap each half in plastic wrap.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel, core and chop apples into small pieces.
Mix together with 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine 2 cups sugar and cooking oil; beat.
Add eggs, orange juice and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour 1/3 batter into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan, alternating with 1/2 apple mixture.
Repeat, ending with layer of batter on top.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack or serving plate to complete cooling.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in bottom of casserole; add onion soup mix, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Bake in covered casserole at 300° for 2 hours.
May be covered with foil.
Punch holes in top to brown.

title: creamy summer fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes before serving.
May substitute 1 cup sliced peaches for orange sections.

title: chess pie *
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients together in small bowl. Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 425° for 10 minutes, then turn oven back to 300° and cook until thick or brown.

title: vitamin drink
directions: Liquify the ingredients.
Season with broth powder or kelp.

title: tex foley's cowboy soup
directions: In a large stockpot, brown the ground beef and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: cocoa light cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, Crisco, salt, cocoa, soda and milk.
Stir in baking powder.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill 6 hours.
Serve on your favorite crackers.

title: broiled doves
directions: Split the birds down the back and flatten breast.
Wipe inside and out with damp cloth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put on a broiler.
When nicely browned, pour generous amounts of melted butter over them.
Serve on toast.

title: tuna fish and potato chip casserole
directions: Smash potato chips into crumbs.
Spread a layer on bottom of 1 1/2-quart round casserole dish.
Add 1 can tuna over potato chips. Add layer of mushroom soup, using 2/3 to 1 can.
Add second layer of potato chips, tuna and mushroom soup, then a third layer.
The last layer is potato chips.
Bake casserole in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain into strips (1/2-inch thick).
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and beef.
Toss and set aside.

title: uncooked fudge
directions: Mix
cocoa and sugar; add margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil;
add vanilla.
Pour over other ingredients; mix well. Drop by spoon and cool.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine cake mix and butter until crumbly.
Add eggs then oats, mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Bake at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat the shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add egg and beat until well mixed.
Add the vanilla and almond extracts.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Stir all together.
Divide the dough and chill.
Grease cookie sheet with salad oil.
Roll 1/4 to 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes or until light brown.

title: cracklin' cowboy cornbread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Mix well. Add milk, eggs and vegetable oil. Stir well into remaining ingredients. Pour batter into a greased skillet (cast-iron). Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until browned.

title: chocolate caramel heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake using directions on box.
Cool.
Poke small holes in cake with spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake, then caramel topping.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crush Heath bars and sprinkle on top.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour part over about 5 pounds of spareribs.
Cook in oven for 2 to 3 hours.
Pour sauce over spareribs about every 1/2 hour.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Pop the popcorn first.
Heat first four ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly, then boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn (use a large foil roasting pan).
Bake at 250° for about 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Stir softened cream cheese and butter together.
Beat with electric mixer, gradually adding sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavorings.
Gradually add flour; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured large tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: fox's cheezy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle a little of the cheese on top.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Use big saucepan.
Mix veggies, broth, water and spices.
Bring to boil and add flour.
Mix well and add chicken.
Bring to boil again.
Mix biscuit package according to directions.
Drop by spoonfuls into pan and simmer, covered, for about 13 minutes.

title: holiday fruit cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom and sides of 12-cup Bundt, fluted tube pan or 10-inch tube (angel food) pan.
In large bowl, combine eggs and water.
Add remaining ingredients by hand; stir until combined. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes; loosen edges and remove from pan.
Cool completely.
To store, wrap tightly in foil or plastic wrap; store in refrigerator.

title: rabbit(zajac pieczony)
directions: Cut rabbit in desired pieces. Dredge with flour and brown in butter.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake in a 350° oven until tender.

title: lisa's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; strain.
Add all ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
It is better if it chills for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Add Italian dressing to suit your taste.
This can also be made with other salad dressings.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend sugar and shortening. Add beaten eggs. Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder and add to first mixture. Stir in vanilla, coconut, nuts and nuts. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix together in small bowl.
Before barbecuing, marinate meat for two hours or more or overnight, turning often to distribute marinade.

title: citrus marinated pork chops
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except pork chops, and mix well.
Add pork chops.
Marinate for at least 30 minutes. Barbecue, fry or bake pork chops as usual.
While chops are cooking, put marinade in a saucepan.
Heat at medium-high, reducing liquid, until thick.
Remove from heat and pour sauce over chops.

title: peanut butter apple dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients; mix well. Serve with apples.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: tailgate salad
directions: Drain veggies. Bring to boil the dressing (sugar, vinegar and oil) and pour over veggies while hot. Refrigerate overnight
or at least 3 to 4 hours. Keeps up to 3 weeks in refrigerator, covered.

title: turkey puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Bake shells on cookie sheet for 20 minutes or until browned and puffed. Combine turkey, soup, milk and pepper in medium saucepan. Heat and stir occasionally while shells are baking. When pastry shells are done, use fork to remove the tops and soft pastry beneath. Reserve the tops. Spoon turkey mixture into shells and top with cheese. Return to oven until cheese is melted.
Serve the stuffed shells garnished with tops removed.

title: quick tomato beef
directions: In skillet, brown beef and drain. Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid into skillet. Add onion, green pepper and cayenne.
Cook over high heat 5 to 8 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring often. Stir in tomatoes and potatoes.
Heat thoroughly. Top with cheese; heat until melted.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine applesauce, melted margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Stir in until smooth the flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in raisins and pecans or walnuts.
Turn batter into well-greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350°
oven for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: white chili
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Place chicken in large saucepan.
Add cold water to cover and bring to a simmer.
Cook until just tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Remove skin; cut into small pieces.
Drain beans.
In same pot, saute onions in oil until they are translucent; stir in garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano, cloves and cayenne; saute 2 minutes.
Add beans, stock and beer.
If desired, stir in optional peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are very tender, about 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add chicken and 1 cup cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Season with salt to taste. Serve with remaining cheese, sour cream and salsa for guests to spoon onto chili if they wish.
Serves 10.

title: easy hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onions until all red is gone from meat. Stir in flour, salts, pepper and mushroom pieces.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soups and simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over cooked and drained wide egg noodles (amount desired for your family).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spicy turkey stir-fry
directions: Saute garlic and vegetables in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until done. Thicken with 1 tablespoon cornstarch, mixed with 2 tablespoons water.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2.

title: grape-nut bread
directions: Put Grape-Nuts in mixing bowl and pour sour milk over Grape-Nuts; let stand 1/2 hour.
Then add your sugar and egg; stir.
Next add your flour, salt, soda and baking powder to mixture. Bake in 350° oven about 40 minutes or until tested with toothpick and it comes out done. I have had this recipe since 1928.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Roll into balls.
Press with fork both ways.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let cool.
Mix together sugars, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add to sugar, oil and egg mixture.
Add oats.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 minutes.

title: everybody loves 'em oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs. Add vanilla.
Set aside.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Mix all together.
Stir in oats.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
(This just makes the dough easier to work with.)
Make into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cookies will be a little gooey in the centers.
Do not bake any longer.
They will firm a little. Leave on cookie sheet for 3 minutes, then place on paper towel until cool.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 cup water.
Combine 1/4 cup of soup mixture, ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, parsley and egg.
Shape into meatballs (1 1/2-inch).
Brown in shortening in skillet.
Pour off drippings.
Add remaining soup mixture.
Cover. Cook over low heat for 15 minutes; stir occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Add a layer of potatoes and a layer of onions until all potatoes and onions are in dish.
Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper through mixture.
Add milk to cover, add butter on top.
Bake 350 until potatoes are cooked through 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
You can add ham or cheese to this for more flavor. Makes 4 servings

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Note:
I do not butter the bread.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and softened cream cheese.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and freeze at least 2 hours.

title: lemon fruit jell candy
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
In a second, place the sugar and corn syrup.

Heat both until a thin foam forms on the first and the second is boiling rapidly for 3 to 5 minutes. Slowly pour the pectin pan into the sugar pan, stirring constantly and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in coloring and nuts; pour immediately into a 9-inch square buttered pan.
Cool to room temperature and invert onto wax paper. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into 3/4-inch squares.
Let stand overnight and pack airtight in storage.
Makes 116.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cook in large saucepan the first 9 ingredients until tender. Mix flour and milk together.
Add milk mixture to other ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Add cubed cheese and let melt. If desired, 3 cups cubed ham may be added.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and spread on top of potatoes.
Bake
30 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in Dutch oven until meat is browned. Add spaghetti sauce and next 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and vegetables.
Return to boil; cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 12 cups.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix 1 layer potato chips, 1 layer tuna, 1 layer potato chip in casserole.
Pour diluted soup over this.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry-lime crepes
directions: Place about 6 strawberry halves in a row in the center of each crepe and roll crepes; set aside.
Heat the butter in chafing dish over canned heat flame and stir in the sugar.
Add the lime juice, stirring constantly, and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Add the crepes and heat through, basting with sauce frequently. Sprinkle crepes with liqueur and ignite.
Shake pan until flames burn out.
Serve crepes with whipped cream and sprinkle with grated rind.

title: ambrosia fruit dip
directions: Mix yogurt and cream of coconut in small serving bowl.
Stir in pecans.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift half of the sugar with the flour 4 times.
Beat egg whites to a foam, add cream of tartar and salt, beat until it holds up in peaks.
Add remaining sugar, a little at a time, beating it in.
Next, add lemon extract and fold in the flour mixture.
Preheat oven to 325° and pour into an ungreased angel cake pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: congealed fruit salad with pretzels
directions: Place broken pretzels in
a 13 x 9 x 2 Pyrex dish and pour melted butter over the top.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350 degrees, stirring twice, let cool.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip, use to cover pretzel layer completely.
Dissolve jello in
water.
Stir in fruit as Jello begins to congeal, then pour over second layer.
Chill until completely set.

title: veggie tortilla pinwheels
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and salad dressing; mix well. Stir in beef, broccoli, cauliflower, onions, and olives. Spread over tortillas. Roll up tightly and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 2 hrs.
Unwrap and cut in 1/2 in. slices.

title: everlasting cole slaw
directions: Cut all of these fine and mix well.
Store covered in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Bake cake in round pans.
Break up 1/2 cake into pieces. Layer cake.
Pour 1/2 syrup over cake, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 Cool Whip, 3 Skor bars in bite size pieces.
Repeat 2nd layer.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Looks nice in a trifle bowl.

title: hot diggety hot dish
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Spray 2 quart casserole dish with Pam.
Cut franks into bite size.
Combine macaroni, franks and remaining ingredients in casserole; then mix well.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tiramisu
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 4 Tbsp. brandy in a metal measuring cup and let stand 5 minutes to soften.
Meanwhile, beat together the 6 egg yolks with 3/4 cup sugar in top of a double boiler.
Add gelatin mixture.
Place over boiling water.

Reduce to simmer and cook while whisking constantly until thermometer registers 160°. Set custard over bowl of ice water and whisk until smooth. Gradually add mascarpone cheese whisking vigorously until well blended.
Beat cream with remaining 1/4 cup sugar to peaks. Fold into mascarpone cheese mixture.
Mix together remaining 2 tablespoons brandy with espresso.
Place one layer of lady fingers on bottom of pan of choice and brush liberally with espresso.
Top with half of cheese mixture.
Sift half of cocoa over layer. Repeat process for 1 more layer using all ladyfingers and espresso.
Cover with saran wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Top with chocolate curls and remaining whipped cream, if desired.

title: apricot-orange bread
directions: Finely shred peel from one orange; reserve peel.
Squeeze juice from all oranges.
Measure 3/4 cup juice; reserve remaining juice.
In mixing bowl, cover apricots with boiling water; let stand about five minutes.
Drain well.
Combine the 3/4 cup juice, 1 teaspoon of the peel, the egg and oil.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add egg mixture; stir just until moistened.
Fold in apricots and nuts.
Turn into 3 greased 6 x 3 x 2-inch loaf pans.

Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove to wire rack to cool completely. Blend 1 tablespoon reserved orange juice with powdered sugar. Add more juice, if necessary, to make a drizzling consistency. Drizzle top of loaves; garnish with reserved orange peel.
Makes 3 loaves.
If you prefer one large loaf, bake in a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: almond tea
directions: Warm tea pot by rinsing with small amount of boiling water. Place tea bags in tea pot.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over tea. Cover and steep 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar, lemon juice and flavorings.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add 2 quarts water.
Stir.
Chill thoroughly and serve over ice.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: easy cooked meringue
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan, stirring well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until transparent and thickened.

title: beef stroganoff(makes 4 to 6 servings.)
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook and stir steak, mushrooms and onion in margarine until steak is browned and vegetables are tender. Reduce heat to medium. Add flour; cook and stir 1 minute. Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup water. Add to mixture. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in sour cream; heat through (do not boil). Serve with hot noodles.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking dish or pan.
Melt butter in a skillet and saute onion and celery until tender.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed; blend well.
Pour into prepared dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according
to directions.
Take a 2-quart casserole dish, put a layer of
macaroni,
then 3 or 4 pats of butter, handful of cubed ham and layer of sliced, boiled eggs. Repeat until casserole dish is
full.
Add
milk until dish is half full with milk.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
(Done when
milk
is
boiling.)
For variety, add grated cheese to layers.

title: cereal snack sacks
directions: Count out and put in a plastic sack 10 pieces of each of the cereals listed.
Shake the bags to mix them up.
Serves 24 to 30 children.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all beans, onion and bacon together.
Add brown sugar and catsup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Peel and chop onion.
Beat the egg.
In a large bowl, combine onion, egg, beef, crumbs, 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce, water, mustard, brown sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour on enough sauce to cover the loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally with remaining sauce.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill.

title: grandmom's mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove stems, leaving caps whole.
Slice stems.
Combine mushrooms and flour in a plastic bag; shake to coat.
Saute mushrooms in butter about 10 minutes.
Add cheese and sour cream, stirring until cheese melts and mixture is blended. Do not boil.

title: oreo layer dessert or dirt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Crush 30 Oreo cookies.
Put in cooking dish and pour butter over.
Bake for 2 minutes at 350°.

title: country fair egg bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine sugar, oil, salt and scalded milk in a large bowl.
Add cold water.
Let cool to lukewarm water.
Stir in eggs and softened yeast.
Add flour gradually to form a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and satiny (5 to 7 minutes).
Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Punch down; let rise 30 minutes.
Divide into 3 parts and form into loaves or rolls.
Place in a greased baking dish and cover.
Let rise 45 minutes for rolls; 1 1/4 hours for loaves. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes for loaves; 15 to 20 minutes for rolls.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: five layer casserole
directions: Place in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 to 10 more minutes.
May take longer to get hamburger done.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Add chocolate to milk and place over low flame.
Cook until mixture is smooth and blended, stirring constantly.
Add sugar and salt and stir until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils. Continue cooking without stirring until a small amount of mixture forms a very soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Cool for a few minutes, then beat it; as it begins to thicken, pour at once into greased pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mrs. kuykendal's magic fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 425° and melt butter in a 9 x 11-inch baking pan. Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and spices.
Gradually add milk.
Pour batter into pan of melted butter.
Pour fruit and juice on top of butter and distribute evenly.
Top with the remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Return pan to oven and bake about 35 to 40 minutes, until batter is brown.
May use canned apples, peaches, berries or cherries.
Frozen fruits are also excellent.
Pop it in the oven and let it cook while the family eats the main course.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole, arrange zucchini slices. In a separate bowl, combine cheese, basil and salt.
Sprinkle over zucchini.
Drizzle oleo over zucchini.
Cook on High, covered, 5 to 7 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Turn dish once during cooking.

title: egg rolls
directions: Saute onion and garlic in frying pan with oil.
Add the other vegetables.
Dice and add fri-chick or chicken to pan.
Cook just a few minutes.
Roll about 2 tablepsoons of the mixture in egg roll skin and fry until brown.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt
butter in baking pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk. Pour over
melted
butter.
Pour
fruit on top.
Do not stir. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chipped ham sandwiches
directions: Boil mustard, sugar, catsup, vinegar and water.
Put chipped ham into mixture and simmer until heated.
Serve in buns.

title: swiss ham kabobs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Combine juice, marmalade, mustard and cloves.
Thread ham, cheese and pineapple on skewers.
Cheese must be between 2 pieces of ham to prevent rapid melting.
Place kabobs 4 to 5 inches from hot coals on grill.
Baste with sauce and grill 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is partially melted.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Pour broth over stuffing. Combine soup and milk.
Toss chicken, onion, celery and stuffing. Mix together with soup, milk and salt. Toss in buttered casserole. Top with buttered crumbs.
Can add a 4 ounce can of mushrooms or peas.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon fromage with raspberry sauce
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add orange juice and refrigerate until consistency of egg whites.
Beat until frothy. Fold in whipped cream and lemon rind.
Pour into lightly oiled and chilled mold.
Chill.
When firm, unmold.
Serve with fresh raspberries and Raspberry Sauce.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Saute chicken in butter and oil until lightly browned.
Remove to casserole dish.
In remaining butter, saute all greens.
Add mushrooms with juice and saute.
Remove from pan and set aside to cool.
After this has cooled, add sour cream.
Then cover chicken with mixture.
Cover and bake at 300°
until chicken is tender, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in pieces approximately 4 x 4-inches or less.
Place in a heavy pot with cover.
Cover with water and cook at a slow boil until color is gone from meat (several hours).

Add onion, celery, green peppers, mushrooms and carrots and continue cooking until meat is tender, then add tomatoes and approximately 2 tablespoons flour or cornstarch, dissolved in hot water or juice of meat.
Let simmer for a few minutes or until liquid thickens.

title: fresh fruit salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.
Serve over fresh fruit salad.

title: sausage-stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the last 3, and mix well. Pack half into 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Arrange sausages in two rows on top.
Pack on remaining mixture on top of first layer, being sure to seal edges all around.
Cover with bacon slices.

title: pecan pie cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients on low speed.
Pat down in greased jelly roll pan. Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Mix the rest of the ingredients real good.
Fold in pecans.
Pour over hot crust. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set at 350°.

title: asparagus platter
directions: On platter or tray, place asparagus; top with bamboo shoots. Sprinkle with Italian dressing.
Top with onion rings.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter and sugar; add vinegar.
Mix remaining ingredients and put in shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chruscik
directions: Add salt to eggs and beat until thick and lemon colored. Add sugar, butter and rum and continue to beat. Fold in flour and knead until dough blisters. Cut in halves; roll very thin and cut into strips about 4-inches long. Slit each piece in center and pull one end through the slit.
Fry in hot fat until lightly browned. Drain on absorbent paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Preheat oven to warm, lowest setting. Heat each tortilla in a skillet until soft. Place on a cookie sheet. Top with meat cheese and vegetables. Any combination. Place in the warm oven. Scramble the eggs. Place on top of the tortilla fillings. Roll them up. Serve warm.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Put garlic powder, salt and pepper on this while browning.
Add sauces to mixture.
Cook noodles.
In a large pan put a layer of sauce on bottom.
Then layer with noodles and cheese; add 1/2 sauce and then repeat. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Melt butter with soup. Add sour cream.
Mix into potatoes. Add 1 cup cheese, onions, salt and pepper.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased with butter) at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and corn flakes on top. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together meat with salt, pepper and baking powder.
Add onion, eggs and tomato juice (1/2 cup milk may be used instead). Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce into mixture.
Add bread crumbs (or mashed potatoes may be substituted for bread).
Knead well until well mixed.
Shape into loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook sugars and cream until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir until cool.
Then beat until creamy and spread on cake quickly.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a large bowl, combine apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the yellow cake mix on the apples.
Toss mixture until evenly coated.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and spoon in apple mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Strain persimmons through a sieve to remove skin and seeds. Mix together with mixer.
Grease 11 x 13-inch pan with the margarine and dot rest of margarine on top of mixture.
Bake at 350°
until done, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Stir all ingredients in bowl with fork until moist.
Beat 1 minute.
Fill loaf pans half full.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Cook mixture 3 minutes.
Cool. Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to cooked mixture.
Mix baking soda with water.
Add to mixture which will be thick.
Beat well. Bake 20 minutes to 1/2 hour in a 350° oven on a 9 x 13-inch cookie tray (greased).
Cut into squares when cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: ground beef and bean casserole
directions: After browning beef with onion, combine with all other ingredients.
You may put in crock-pot and cook on low for 2 to 3 hours or cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour, stirring halfway.
It tastes better cooked in crock-pot.

title: cucumber and cheese sandwiches
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Peel, seed and mince cucumber.
Mix cheese and cucumber with onion, salt and pepper.
Spread on bread. Can be cut into halves or quarters.
Will keep a number of days in refrigerator.
Yields enough filling for 1 1/2 pound loaf of bread.

title: cabbage and noodle casserole
directions: Fry bacon until brown. Add cabbage mixed with onion.
Cover tightly and stew until done.
Cook noodles and drain.
Stir into cabbage mixture. Serve hot. One tablespoon caraway seed may be added, if desired.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Put the meat in a heavy 11-inch skillet.
Slice potatoes, carrots and onion in layers on top of it.
Cover with soup. Cover and cook over medium heat about 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and cook 30 more minutes.
Put cheese on top and let melt just before serving.
Enjoy!

title: bean salad(good)
directions: Combine beans, celery, tomato and onion; toss.
Combine picante sauce, dressing and mustard to one's taste; mix well. Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Cover and marinate overnight.

title: pie glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: pastry chili
directions: Thaw pastry sheets so they are pliable but not completely thawed.
Spray foil with cooking oil to prevent pastry from sticking.
Place one sheet on foiled cookie sheet.
Put as much chili and cheese on sheet as you desire.
Cover with second pastry sheet.
Seal edges.
You may need to wet edges to seal them.
Bake at 400 for 25 minutes.
Then bake at 350 for another 20 minutes.

title: sausage potatoes
directions: Crumble sausage and fry until brown; drain and rinse with hot water.
Peel and cube potatoes; boil until tender.
Drain and return to pan.
Mix potatoes, sausage, soup, mushrooms, onions, milk and 1 cup of the Cheddar cheese.
Mix until cheese is melted and potatoes are well coated, taking care not to mash potatoes too much.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of cheese over top.
Place back in oven until cheese is melted.
Garnish with chopped scallions and serve.

title: chicken pie 1(quick and easy)
directions: Place deboned chicken in baking dish.
Put butter and broth on stove to melt.
Beat in eggs and crumbled toast.
Pour this mixture over chicken and bake in oven until brown at 350° to 375°.

title: sweet potato biscuit
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar, shortening to sweet potatoes while hot.
Combine to flour mixture. Knead for 1 minute.
Roll out to 3/4 inch thick.
Cut and bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cover stewing beef with water and simmer 4 hours.
Pour off excess water (excellent soup stock).
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix good.
Serve on split buttered bun.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and cream of tartar; mix well.
Boil until mixture spins a fine thread.
Remove from heat and pour over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: beef parmesan
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Mix flour, salt and pepper and dredge meat in seasoned flour.
Pound meat on both sides.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and basil.
Dip meat into egg and water mixture, then dredge in crumb mixture, coating evenly.
Brown in oil; drain on paper towels and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce, garlic, sugar and oregano.
Pour over meat.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove foil and top each piece of meat with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake additional 3 to 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: fruit balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with rolling pin. Mix with rest of ingredients. Roll out in small balls, then roll ball in confectioners (4x or 10x) sugar. Refrigerate overnight. Take out. Reroll in sugar and serve. Can be frozen. Let thaw, then reroll in sugar.

title: turkey burgers deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place into 4 patties.
Set oven to broil or 550°.
Cook patties for 3 to 4 minutes on each side for rare; 6 to 7 minutes for medium.
Serves 4.

title: hot mustard
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar and let set overnight.
Make sure the pan is non-reactive.
Add remaining ingredients and cook in double boiler until mixture thickens, stirring often. Keep refrigerated.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, oregano and green pepper.
Layer noodles, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cool whip fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: pistachio cake (2)
directions: Mix together sour cream, cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and oil. Beat well after each egg.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into a greased and floured angel food cake pan.
Combine nuts, sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle half of this mixture over batter in pan.
Pour remaining batter on top of cinnamon mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fish - fire island style
directions: In a large baking dish with cover, place spinach on bottom of baking dish.
Next place rinsed and dried fillet (fish) on top. Add sliced tomatoes and onions.
On top of that, sprinkle with oregano, garlic, lemon juice and add salt and pepper to taste. Cover and bake approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: korean marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put meat (chicken, short ribs) into marinade and chill, covered, for 4 to 5 hours or longer.
Makes marinade for 4 pounds of meat.

title: red raspberry cake and icing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and eggs (one at a time). Don't overbeat.
Break up 1/2 package of frozen raspberries (save other 1/2 for icing) and add to batter.
Bake at 350° until golden.
For best results, use 3 (8-inch) cake pans.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs thick and add gradually.
Add oil and chocolate and blend well.
On low speed, add dry ingredients and stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer potatoes and onions.
Top with soup and milk mixture.
Salt and pepper; dot with margarine and paprika for color.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour covered, then an extra 15 minutes uncovered.

title: melt in your mouth cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and egg.
Beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients and nuts; mix well.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Place far apart; these cookies spread.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for about 5 minutes.
Let cool a little before removing onto waxed paper. Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: golden nut cups
directions: Blend butter, cheese and flour.
Make 24 balls and put one each in small muffin pan and press to sides with fingers.

title: dreamy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend Ricotta and cream cheese together.
In separate bowl, beat eggs until lemony.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Add to cheese mixture and mix well.
Combine flour and cornstarch.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Add sour cream and mix well.

title: barbecued sausage balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into 2 dozen 1-1/2-inch balls.
Brown in ungreased skillet and pour off fat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: butter and bacon potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; cook until tender. Melt butter and onion until tender. Cook bacon. Drain potatoes. Add salt and pepper; then top with butter and bacon.

title: chicken wings
directions: Put soy sauce in large container. Add equal amount of water. Add garlic powder, onion powder, pepper and sugar. Mix thoroughly. Season to taste. Put chicken in liquid. Marinate for at least 1 1/2 hours. Put wings under broiler for 15 minutes. Turn over and broil for 10 minutes.

title: favorite great northern beans
directions: First clean beans in colander; set aside.
Take medium pan and fry bacon, then chop onions.
Throw them in pot, then put 6 cups water.
Throw ham in pot and let boil real good, then throw beans in.
Boil for 25 minutes, then turn off the heat for 1 hour.
Turn back on and cook until the color of the beans is given off in the juice.
Always keep plenty of water in pot to keep from burning beans.

title: christmas jam cake
directions: Sift together the flour, cocoa, salt, baking powder and soda. Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs. Alternately add the sifted ingredients and milk.
Then add jam, nuts and raisins.
Mix well and pour into greased, floured pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Put pan of water in oven while cake is cooking.
When it is cold, pour 1 jigger of bourbon over each layer.
This can be stored in a tight container. It's moist, light and rich.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Shape into bite size balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 48 servings.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add chili powder, cumin and tomatoes; simmer until thick, 1 hour or longer.
Add 1 cup cooked pinto beans for each pound meat.
Serves 40 to 50 people.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Wash beef to remove brine.
Place in large kettle.
Cover with water and slowly bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove scum. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Skim fat.
Return to rolling boil. Add whole onions, carrots, potatoes and parsnips.
Reduce heat and cook gently, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Core and cut cabbage in eighths.
Add cabbage and cook 20 minutes.
Transfer meat to platter.
Arrange vegetables around meat.
Yields 8 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs until bubbles begin to form and gradually add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Pie is done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.)

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Trim ends of eggplant and slice into unpeeled rounds 1/4-inch thick.
Place on baking sheet or broiler pan in a single layer. Brush with oil, if desired, and broil about 5 minutes, until lightly brown.
Turn and brown other side.

title: salmon patties
directions: Work into patties and fry.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Add turkey, 3 ounces of cheese and rice.
Stir until cheese melts. Place in 8 x 8-inch baking dish that has been sprayed.
Sprinkle with remainder of cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach in microwave on High for 6 minutes, turning 1/4 turn halfway.
Squeeze excess water from spinach.
Mix all ingredients.
Make into small balls.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°. These can be easily frozen before baking.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Bag and cook later, but thaw before baking.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Turn filling into large, rectangular baking dish.
(For easy clean-up, spray dish with Pam.)
Mix flour and milk together until lumps are gone.
Add melted butter and stir vigorously.
Pour crust mixture over filling.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix dry yeast with warm water.
Add sugar; set aside 5 to 10 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel and slice onions 1/4 inch thick.
Separate rings and chill in a bowl of ice water 1 hour.
Drain onions; dry thoroughly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: spam special
directions: Cut Spam into 1/2 x 1/2-inch squares.
Cut green pepper into equal sizes, 1/2 x 1/2-inch.
Lightly fry Spam and pepper together until lightly brown and tender.
Add can of chunk pineapple with syrup; simmer until juice thickens.
Serve over cooked white rice. Serves 6.

title: popular butter rolls
directions: In a large bowl, soak yeast in water.
Mix in sugar, butter, eggs and salt.
Beat in 1 cup flour, then mix in enough flour to make a stiff dough. Mix well.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning to grease top and sides of dough.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Shape rolls and place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake in a 400° oven 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
If desired, unbaked rolls may be frozen and baked later.

title: quick supper pizza burgers
directions: Take english muffins, split in half and put on 2 cookie sheets.
Add the sauce, then the sausage and 2 pcs.
pepperoni. Top with mozzarella cheese.
Preheat oven to 300° and bake long enough to melt the cheese.
Ready to eat.
Makes about 24.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chips and butter in heavy saucepan.
Add powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Allow sauce to cool slightly and then pour into jars.
When completely cool, screw on lids.

title: macaroni and cheese salad in pepper cups
directions: Clean 6 green peppers.
Mix all other ingredients together. Stuff into peppers.
Garnish with egg wedges or radish roses. Chill and serve.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°; grease lightly or line cupcake pan.
In a 2-cup measuring cup, measure yogurt, oil and egg; stir to combine.
In a large bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Add yogurt mixture to flour mixture, stirring approximately 25 strokes.
Fill muffin tins to the rim.
Bake for 20 minutes or until springy when gently pressed.

title: cheese ball
directions: Melt margarine and Cheddar cheese together over low heat.
It will separate.
Add a little garlic salt, if desired.
Mix cream cheese with melted mixture.
Completely cream together.
Put in refrigerator until gooey.
Form a ball; roll in chopped nuts. Needs to set out 6 hours before serving.

title: fried fish
directions: In a bowl, mix mustard, egg and hot sauce.
Marinate fillets in this mixture for 15 minutes.
Season flour and cornmeal with Tony's seasoning, garlic powder and red pepper.
Roll fish in flour mixture and coat well.
Fry at 350° until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: cheese cake
directions: Press 1 package crescent rolls in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Whip cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Pour over crust.
Top with other package of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drizzle with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: pickled eggs
directions: In saucepan, blend mustard with a little vinegar.
Add remaining vinegar, water, and next 5 ingredients.
Cover.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over onions and eggs.
Cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on relish tray.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugars, shortening and eggs; beat for 2 minutes on medium speed of electric mixer.
Add pumpkin.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and spices; gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except onion and poppy seed, in order listed; blend in mixer until thickened.
Add onion and poppy seed; stir well.
Store in refrigerator.
Before using, remove and let it get to room temperature.

title: best italian spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Rinse the first 4 ingredients well.
Saute them with the next 3 ingredients until extremely crystallized.
Saute ground chuck, spice mix and 1 cup vegetable oil until brown; pour off grease. Next add garlic.
Mix together with vegetables.
Warm last 3 ingredients in a large pot to approximately 180°, stirring constantly.
Add all ingredients and stir.
Add 2 tablespoons flaked red pepper and stir.
Turn off the heat, touch the bottom of the pot gently with a spoon.
If the spoon sticks, check for possible burning.
Use burn precaution method.
Place the covered pot in the walk-in to cool.

title: sunny day punch
directions: Instead of using ice, freeze wedges of fresh oranges or lemon to float atop the punch.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with Pam. Mix all ingredients in large bowl until just blended; pour mixture into pan.
Recipe can be prepared up to this point one or two days ahead of time.
This saves time and allows the flavor to absorb better.
Before baking, mix tomato sauce and brown sugar; pour over top.
If you'd like, slice the remaining bell pepper half and add to the tomato sauce.
Smooth top; bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup of the cake mix.
Mix the remaining mix, margarine and egg together until crumbly.
Pat in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan to make the crust.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on back of box.
Pinch up mandarin oranges and put in batter.
Pour a little of juice in batter. Bake as directed and cool.

title: deviled shrimp
directions: Melt butter
and saute onions until transparent, adding garlic the
last
minute.	Add
mustard, seasonings, flour and shrimp, stirring constantly.
Add
milk
or
broth	and cook 2 minutes, stirring
constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the chopped eggs.
Spoon
into individual crab shells or ramekins. Cover the top
with
mixture	of
crumbs
and Parmesan cheese. Bake in preheated
oven
at
about 30 minutes.
This can also be baked in a greased casserole.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Combine honey and mustard; refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Clean and peel shrimp.
Cut in butterfly fashion. Allow shrimp to marinate in the prepared sauce for several hours. Place shrimp on grill that has been prepared with aluminum foil. Grill until golden.

title: date candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk until forms a ball.
Add the nuts, dates and vanilla; beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into a buttered platter; cut into squares.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and
milk to a boil.
Cook until soft ball. Take off
stove
and
add
peanut butter, butter and vanilla. Pour in pan immediatly.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt. Cut in
margarine with knives until crumbly. Add heavy cream slowly until all is mixed well and you can form 2 balls of dough.
Flatten each ball of dough and store in a plastic food storage bag or Saran Wrap.
Place in refrigerator for at least 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: tasty fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Serve with sliced apples, pears, peaches, grapes and strawberries.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: veggie squares
directions: Separate rolls into 8 sections and spread on a cookie sheet pinching seams together.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.	Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and envelope of ranch dressing together.
Spread mixture over crust.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables over mixture.
Cover with grated cheddar cheese.
Slice and serve.
Makes 15 - 20 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add all 3 soups and taco sauce. Keep onion and cheese in separate bowls.

title: white beans
directions: Sort and wash white beans. After they are clean, fill pot with water and boil beans until they start to split open (about 1 hour). While this is cooking, fry onions and onion tops down until they are clear (on medium heat). Once beans are split, drain and fill pot again with more water. Put beans back to boil and cook on high heat. Add onion

mixture to pot. Sprinkle parsley flakes. Let cook until thick, but remember to smash beans on side of pot for creamy ones and to lower the heat as they become thick. Watch not to scorch the bottom (that's why you lower the heat as you go).

title: grits
directions: Cook water, milk, salt and grits until thick.
Add cheese, eggs and butter; pour in baking dish.
Put corn flakes on top; dot with butter.
Cook 60 minutes at 350°.

title: melt-in-your-mouth sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, salad oil and vanilla. Mix until smooth.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (barely begin to brown).

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix thoroughly and put in hot buttered and floured iron skillet or cook in muffin pan. Spread thin for better potato bread. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until golden brown. (Time may vary according to thickness of bread.)

title: pork and water chestnut meatballs
directions: Mix together ground pork, finely chopped water chestnuts, green onion, garlic, egg, 1 teaspoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Blend well.
Shape meat into balls, 1-inch in diameter.
Roll in cornstarch.
Heat oil in pan.
Saute meatballs 10 minutes until browned on both sides.
Set aside.

title: chicken breasts in orange sauce(serves 6)
directions: Flour chicken and lightly brown in oil.
Blend all ingredients, except carrots and mushrooms, in a large Dutch oven. Add carrots, mushrooms and chicken to blended ingredients and cook over a medium, low heat, 40 to 50 minutes.
Carrots should be done and crisp, but make sure chicken is not overdone as it will become dry.
Serves 6.
Perfect main dish for company.
Serve over rice pilaf.

title: mexi-corn lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Add corn, tomato sauce, salsa, chili powder and cumin.
In bowl	combine
other	ingredients except tortillas and Cheddar cheese.
Arrange
tortillas on bottom and up sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 the meat mixture, cheese mixture on meat, 6 tortillas
layer next.
Top with	meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for	30
minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and serve.

title: grandma's bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Soak overnight in a brine, to cover, made of 1 tablespoon salt and 1 quart water.
Mix the remaining ingredients with the vinegar and bring to boiling point.
Drain brine from cukes.
Pack in jars with the boiling hot liquid and seal.

title: cranberry applesauce jello
directions: Mix together the jello and hot water.
Mash up the cranberry sauce and add it and the applesauce to the jello mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan and refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water and 1 3/4 cups cold water. Add pineapple and sliced bananas.
Stir and pour in 13 x 9-inch pan; top with marshmallows and place in refrigerator to set.

title: overnight lasagne
directions: In large skillet, brown meat; drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta, chives, oregano and eggs.
Mix well.

title: old fashioned ambrosia
directions: Note:
Garnish with cherry halves for color.

title: steve and anita's biscuits
directions: Mix flour and shortening together with a pastry blender until mixture is a coarse meal. Add milk, a little at a time. This will be a soft dough. Turn out on a lightly floured board. Pat into a 6 x 8-inch rectangle, about 1 1/2-inches thick. Cut into rectangles with a floured knife. Place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake in a preheated 500° oven for 8 to 10 minutes. Brush with melted butter as soon as they come out of the oven. Enjoy!

title: chocolate freezer cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 thin layers in 9 x 13-inch pan by directions on box.
Let cool on rack and then cut cakes in half to have 4 layers.
Mix 1/4 cup milk and 1/4 cup flour and cook well.
Set aside and let the mixture get cold.
Mix butter, Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Beat all together well, then stir in Cool Whip.
Put this mixture between cooled cake layers and freeze.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread on cookie sheet or buttered pan. Refrigerate until cooled and hardened.
Cut into bars.

title: bird nests
directions: In bowl, combine cereal and coconut; set aside.
Mix and bring to a boil the remaining ingredients.
Stir into cereal mixture. Let cool.
Shape into Bird Nests and fill with jelly bean "eggs."

title: easy sugar cream pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Dissolve cornstarch in milk, then add to first mixture. Cook until thick.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Put in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Let set.

title: spicy pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Mix well.

title: carrot casserole
directions: In heavy saucepan, cook diced onion until clear in margarine. Add flour.
Stir mixture until it bubbles. Add milk slowly. Bring to slow boil until thick. Add cheese and stir constantly until melted. Grease casserole. Layer carrots, putting sauce on each layer.
Put bread crumbs on last layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: autumn soup
directions: Cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce to simmer and simmer 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until done.

title: scout s'mores(single serving)
directions: Toast marshmallow.
Place 4 sections of chocolate on 1 graham cracker square.
Place toasted marshmallow on top of chocolate. Place remaining graham cracker square on top of marshmallow.
Eat like a sandwich.

title: taco dip
directions: In baking dish, spread can of refried beans.
Then spread fried hamburger on top of this.
Put grated cheese on top of this and pour jar of sauce on top of this.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix well. Pour into buttered pan.

title: steak in sour cream sauce
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
In large pan brown meat in hot oil.
Drain excess oil.
Add onion, mushrooms and water.
Reduce heat and simmer; cover 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, avoid boiling, adding sour cream and parsley.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Blend cheese, pineapple, 1 cup pecans, pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Chill well.
Garnish with pineapple slices, cherry and parsley. Surround with crackers.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add to sour cream.
Serve over fresh fruit.

title: dieter's lasagna
directions: In large skillet, combine 1/2 cup water, onion, celery and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender and water has evaporated, about 10 minutes.
Add ground steak and saute until browned.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, parsley, oregano, basil and salt.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered and stirring occasionally, 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles as package label directs.
Also, combine cottage cheese and egg in small bowl; stir until well blended.
Preheat oven to 350°. Place 3 noodles in bottom of 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Top with half of cheese mixture, then with half of meat sauce.
Repeat.
Arrange Mozzarella on top; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until very hot and golden brown.
Let lasagna stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings, 271 calories each.

title: quesadilla pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Place 4 tortillas on baking sheet. Sprinkle cheddar cheese evenly over tortillas; top with remaining tortillas. Brush lightly with oil. Bake for 4 minutes. Combine pizza sauce and cumin in small bowl; spread on tortillas. Spoon beans evenly over sauce mixture; sprinkle with chilies, green onions Monterey jack cheese and bake for 3 minutes or until cheese is melted. Cut into wedges.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Rinse, dry and slice mushrooms.
In a large nonstick frypan, heat butter and add mushrooms, onions, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
