Uncover, stir in flour and cheese and cook about 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn into 9-inch buttered pan.
Spread evenly.
Mix half and half with beaten egg yolks and pour over mushrooms.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: beer beans for gang
directions: Mix all ingredients and let soak overnight.
If you need to, add water in the morning to about 1-inch above beans.
Never add cold water after beans have started to cook or they will get hard. I usually cook mine in the crock-pot for 10 to 12 hours.
Crock-pot is full to brim.
You may wish to set a container underneath in case of overflow.
Beans can be frozen in smaller portions for later use.

title: meat loaf plus
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Mix thoroughly.
Transfer mixture to greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake until meat loaf shrinks from sides of pan and top is brown, about 1 hour.
Turn out onto platter and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in seasoned water for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Remove chicken in chunks.
Mix chicken with sour cream and soup. Put in a greased casserole.
Mix bread stuffing with water or broth.
Put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: cherry surprise
directions: Lay sliced angel food cake on bottom of pan.
Next, a layer of pudding, then cream cheese mixture.
Pour can of sweetened cherries on top.
Last, top with Cool Whip.

title: cookies 'n cream squares(a delicious cheesecake treat)
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°F. Place 30 of the cookies in food processor container; cover. Process 30 to 45 seconds or until finely ground.
Add butter; mix well. Press onto bottom of 13x9-inch baking pan.

title: barbecue sauce(excellent for pork barbecue or spareribs)
directions: Brown onions in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour over bread crumbs.
Cook chicken soup, Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice until mixed.
Cook chicken breasts and broccoli (drain).
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour mixture over chicken breasts and broccoli.
Put bread crumbs and butter on top.
Put in 350° preheated oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly brown.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve jello flavors separately, using 1 cup hot water in lemon jello.
Two cups hot water in each lime and raspberry jello. Dissolve each.
Stir marshmallows into lemon jello; set aside. Add 1 1/2 cups cold water to lime and raspberry jello.
Pour lime jello into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Set raspberry jello aside at room temperature.
Then add cream cheese to lemon mixture; beat until well blended.
Blend in mayonnaise, whipped cream and crushed pineapple.
Chill until very thick.
Spoon gently over lime jello.
Chill until set.

title: creole cabbage(soup)
directions: Combine and cook until cabbage is done, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: corn and crab soup
directions: Blend together margarine and flour over low heat.
Add onion; saute until wilted.
Add remaining ingredients (except for crabmeat) and cook on medium heat for 40 minutes.
Add crabmeat 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 7 or 8.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add all ingredients.
Cook slowly until onions are tender.
Add a little water, if necessary.
Place chicken pieces on outdoor grill and slosh sauce on chicken.
Slosh again before turning chicken.
Slosh after turning chicken. Repeat the sloshing and turning every 10 minutes for approximately 1 hour or more depending on the size of the chicken pieces.
Do not overcook or chicken will become dry.

title: florida chow chow(cold salad)
directions: Mix sugar, salt, pepper and water.
Add vinegar and oil. Bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Add vegetables and refrigerate.

title: cornbread pot pie
directions: Fry hamburger until done.
Add onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Drain.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add vegetables and drained tomatoes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Mix cornbread according to directions.
Pour over cheese and vegetables.
Bake at 350° until cornbread is done.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Blend cocoa into melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Top with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream and garnish with nuts, cherries and shaved chocolate. Keeps well.

title: hush puppies
directions: 1. Mix all and spoon a
heaping tablespoon at a time in hot oil.

title: bacon 'n egg pancake roll-up
directions: Prepare pancakes using pancake mix.
Cut 8 slices of bacon into pieces, 1 inch long.
Panfry until lightly browned.
Drain. Cook 8 additional bacon slices; drain and keep warm.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot oil; roll up using cheese, minced onion and green chili. Place in baking dish and pour all the cream of chicken soup diluted with water. Bake at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: turtle sauce piquante
directions: Parboil turtle meat for a short time.
Drain and season.
Melt margarine and brown meat until it begins to stick.
Add vegetables and saute.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and about 1 pint of water.
Cook 2 to 3 hours, until tender.
Add mushrooms.
Serve over hot rice.

title: fried fish batter
directions: Melt Crisco in pan.
Should be very hot before fish are put in; salt and pepper fish.
Mix pancake mix as directed on box, omitting milk and substituting it with the same amount of 7-Up. Coat fish in batter and fry.
Makes a very crisp, light brown batter.

title: savory meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, bread crumbs and salt.
Shape into about 20 small meatballs.
Brown meatballs in cooking oil in skillet.
Add soup, water, peas and 1/2 teaspoon
salt.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: old fashion chocolate pie
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind onions, cabbage, green tomatoes, red and green peppers. Add salt and mix well. Let stand overnight.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water.
Add cheese (cut in chunks) and butter.
Stir until both are melted.
Add egg and milk mixture. Mix well.
Pour into well greased baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees until firm and light brown on top.

title: gerschus butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter, add brown sugar, heat just to boiling. Remove from heat, cool, and add egg yolks, flour, milk, and salt. Bring to boil over direct heat, stirring constantly, then place over hot water for 10-15 min. Add vanilla. Pour filling into baked pie shell.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften. Cream, chill and roll in chopped nuts.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Cream the butter well.
Add sugar; mix, then add eggs, then flavoring.
Combine flour and salt; do not overbeat.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then turn out of pan.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Stir salt and flour in mixing bowl.
Rub in margarine with fingertips until mixture is consistency of dried bread crumbs. Add 1 ounce sugar.
Add cold water, a little at a time, until mixture forms dough.
Roll half the dough on a floured board and line a well-greased pie dish with the dough.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: *Additional strawberries and mint for garnish, if desired.

title: turkey pizza
directions: Brown ground turkey and Italian seasoning.
Spread dough in pan.
Add pizza sauce.
Crumble turkey over sauce.
Add black olives and mushrooms and then cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix thawed spinach, soup mix and sour cream together.
Place in casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crock-pot mexican dish
directions: Brown meat and add onion and beans.
Layer in crock-pot: Doritos, meat mixture, cheese, etc.
Pour soup and tomatoes over top of layers.
Cover and cook until bubbles.

title: chocolate sheet cake with fudge frosting
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and chocolate syrup.
Add salt.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. Frost with hot Fudge Frosting.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Mash up.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir well.
Add pepper, cheese, sugar, margarine, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Add crackers and stir.
Butter sides of baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Last 10 minutes, add a few crumbled crackers on top.

title: dish of dirt
directions: In each of 4 dessert cups, place 2 tablespoons cookie crumbs. Top each with 1/2 cup ice cream, then remaining 2 tablespoons crumbs and 1 tablespoon syrup.
Garnish with gummy worms and whipped topping.

title: bunny biscuits
directions: Separate biscuits; place 5 of them on a greased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Cut remaining biscuits in half.
Shape biscuit halves to form ears and firmly attached to whole biscuit. On each biscuit, press on 2 raisin eyes, 1 candy nose and 4 slivered almond whiskers.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until biscuits are browned.
Cool slighlty; frost ears with icing. Yields 5 biscuits.

title: "better than sex" cake
directions: 1. Make German chocolate cake mix according to directions in two 9-inch rounds.
When finished baking, poke holes in cake (about the size of a straw). 2. In a bowl pour in the sweetened condensed milk and caramel ice cream topping.
Mix well and spread between two rounds.
Pour chocolate chips on top of cake and spread until melted. 3. Sprinkle pecans, let cool.
Spread coolwhip over cake, sprinkle Score Bars on top.
ENJOY!

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for several hours.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips or chunks.
Cook chicken and onion in 1 Tbsp. oil until done.
Add the cooked rice.
Add soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir together.

title: overnight english pea salad
directions: Layer, beginning and ending with lettuce. Spread mayonnaise over top in a thin, even layer. Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top of salad. Refrigerate overnight. Sprinkle bacon on top just before serving.

title: pat's cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oil in a large frypan.
Add potatoes, onion and green peppers; cover pan.
Cooking time is approximately 30 minutes. Stir often until potatoes are soft and brown.
Once the potatoes have cooked, turn heat off and cover the potatoes with cheese. Cover the pan and allow time for the cheese to melt.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked chicken
directions: Line dish with dried beef.
Wrap each piece of chicken with a piece of uncooked bacon.
Place chicken in dish.
Mix the soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cook, uncovered, at 250° for 4 hours.

title: coq au vin
directions: Coat chicken in seasoned flour.
Brown in butter; remove and place in 3-quart casserole.
Brown shallots, mushrooms and garlic. Add to casserole.
Saute onions; cover and cook until tender. Add to casserole the onions, bacon, wine, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Serve with border of croutons.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Put blueberries and 3/4 cup of sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Spread dry cake mix on top of blueberries.
Drizzle margarine on top of mix. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of sugar and pecans evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt; cook for 1 minute. Add peanut butter.
Add oats and flavoring; mix real good.
Spread out on tinfoil; let cool.
Almost like candy.

title: mediterranean salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients;
toss gently.

title: easy sos
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper to taste; drain well. With meat in skillet, pour in the cream of chicken soup and 1/2 cup water.
Cook on low for about 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon-spiced ginger crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Three hours before, mix at low speed all ingredients until moistened, then mix at medium for 2 minutes. Wrap dough in waxed paper, refrigerating for 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, divide dough into 72 equal pieces.
Roll a piece into ball.
Coat a ball with sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten ball with bottom of a glass to 1/8-inch thick circle.
Sprinkle slightly with sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned around edges.
Cool 2 minutes, then carefully remove to wire racks.
Cool.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: fast and fruity salad
directions: Combine pie filling and can of fruit.
Mix in other fruits and nuts.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.
Almost eliminates dessert!!!

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour both cans of cherry pie filling into cake pan.
Melt butter and mix with cake mix.
Spread over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: peach soup
directions: Add spices to 2 cups water.
Add peaches; cook until tender. Press through colander.
Put back into water.
Boil a few minutes. Add wine and sugar.
Heat to under boiling.
Serve with croutons. Serves 8.

title: fruit pizza
directions: You will need 12-inch pizza pan.

title: apple pancake
directions: Peel and core apples.
Slice and saute in 1/3 cup butter for 5 minutes.
Mix sugar and spices and add to apples.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix eggs, milk, flour and salt.
Beat with rotary beater for 2 minutes.
Heat 1 to 2 tablespoons batter in 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake in preheated very hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
As soon as batter puffs up in center, puncture with fork, repeating as often as necessary.
Lower heat to 350° and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread warm apple mixture over whole surface of pancake.
May use more sugar and butter when serving or serve as is.
Serves 4.

title: eva's meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, blend well the ground meat mixture, salt, pepper, garlic, onion, bread and 2 of the eggs.
Pat onto sheet, 8 x 14 inches, on a piece of foil.
Combine Feta and spinach; spread evenly over meat mixture.
Roll up, starting at 8-inch side, using foil to help the process.
Place, seam side down, on greased pan. Bake in preheated moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding food coloring last.

title: flan
directions: Heat sugar
in	heavy saucepan until it becomes liquid. Pour into flan
pan (2 quart Pyrex bowl with rounded bottom is okay). Coat pan sides with sugar.	Combine remaining ingredients and blend
until
smooth.
Pour
into
flan
pan.
Set in large pan filled with
water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted
in center comes out clean.
Refrigerate until cold. Invert onto platter just before serving.

title: pickled red beet eggs
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: maple peanut softies
directions: Mix together peanut butter, maple syrup and milk powder. Spread mixture into loaf pan.
Pat down to make even layer. Sprinkle peanuts over mixture.
Press them to make them stick. Chill 1 hour. Cut into squares. Keep refrigerated when not serving them.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble crackers finely.
Line bottom of casserole dish with half
of
crackers.
Mix
all
other
ingredients, except margarine, together.
Pour onto crumbs.
Top with other crumbs and pats of margarine.	Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: breakfast egg
directions: Pam spray 9 x 12 pan (glass or metal).
Then press crescent rolls into pan (to make a pocket/dish).
Cut sausage into small bite-size and place all over the rolls.
Mix milk with eggs and pour into pan.
Bake at 425° for fifteen minutes or until done.

title: filled picnic cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Fill 24 cupcake liners 1/2 full.
Mix cream cheese, egg, sugar and chocolate bits together.
Place generous teaspoonful on batter.
Top with rest of batter.
Bake according to package directions for cupcakes.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Mix the cornstarch and soy sauce together first.
Place the chicken in the cornstarch mixture and stir until chicken is thoroughly coated.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Heat oil in wok over high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry until browned.
Remove the chicken from the wok.
Put the broccoli and onion in the wok and stir-fry for two minutes.
Add the mushrooms and bean sprouts.
Return the chicken to the wok.
Stir in chicken broth; cover and cook gently for five minutes or until the vegetables are crisp and tender.
Serve with rice.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 cup hot water.
Drain the cans of fruit. Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator.

title: swiss enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add garlic, tomato sauce, chilies, chicken and seasoning to taste.
Mix sour cream, chicken broth and cream.
Dip tortillas in cream sauce.
Spoon chicken mixture on tortilla.
Roll and place in greased baking dish.
Pour cream sauce over enchiladas.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered with foil.
Remove foil to brown.
May be garnished with avocado slices or ripe olives.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: picante sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Cook for one hour.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cut into each other using two bread knives.
Makes 4 small or 2 large balls.
Cover with parsley, chives or chopped walnuts. Chill 3 hours.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots; cook about 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Add onion and green pepper.
Heat tomato soup and add sugar to dissolve.
Stir in oil, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and seasonings.
Marinate for 3 to 5 days in refrigerator.
Put in double boiler so it can be heated, or it can be served cold.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and 2 cups flour together and pat in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat together eggs, lemon juice, sugar, flour and salt.
Pour over crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
While warm, sprinkle powdered sugar over top.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Boil water, sugar, shortening and mincemeat for 3 minutes. Let cool.
Dissolve salt and soda in cup of boiling water.
Let cool and add to mincemeat mixture.
Add flour and baking powder. Bake at 350° until done, about 40 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook the
onion and green pepper in the margarine until tender.
Blend
in	the
soup
and milk, then add the chicken, pimento and
pepper.
Heat over low heat, stirring frequently. Serve over toasted waffles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Select sweet potatoes of approximately the same size for uniform cooking.
Scrub potatoes and remove any spots with a sharp knife.
Prick surface with a fork.
Place 1-inch apart on paper plate in microwave oven.
Cook about 12 minutes on High power or until tender.
Peel and slice when cool enough to handle.
Arrange in a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: blueberry juice
directions: Using a juicer, process all ingredients together.
Serve in tall glass.
Makes 1 serving.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to instructions and bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine undrained pineapple and sugar.
Heat until mixture comes to boil (approximately 2 minutes).
When cake is done, remove from oven and puncture all over with fork.
Pour pineapple over hot cake.
Let cool.
Make pudding according to instructions.
Fold in sour cream.
Spread over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts, if desired.

title: zucchini deluxe cake
directions: Cream together margarine, cooking oil and sugar.

Add eggs, vanilla, sour milk, cocoa, flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Beat all with a mixer, then add zucchini and stir in the mixture. Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Sprinkle generously over the top with chocolate chips and 2 rounded tablespoonfuls of sugar over chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Should be refrigerated.
Whip cream or ice cream is especially good with it.

title: beans 'n wiener biscuit casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In	medium	saucepan,
combine wieners, pork and beans, catsup,
onions
and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon
hot
bean mixture into greased, 8 or 9-inch square pan.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut vegetables and cover with water in a 12-quart pot.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Cover, lower heat and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Melt Cheez Whiz in melted margarine.
Add soup and stir well.
Stir in broccoli and rice. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange carrot breakfast drink("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender container.
Cover and blend at high speed until carrots are liquefied.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Place loaf of bread dough on cookie tray in a warm place to raise.
Preheat oven to 350° before rolling out dough to 1/4-inch thick circle.
In center of dough, layer 1/2 of the pepperoni and 1/2 of the cheese.
Fold over one edge of circle to cover meat and cheese.
Layer remaining meat and cheese.
Cover with last of bread dough.
Pinch edges together and place on ungreased cookie tray. Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice when cool.
May be reheated when served.

title: liver and bacon pate
directions: Grind bacon and liver in grinder, using fine disc.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Yields 2 cups.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Season chicken breast halves with oregano, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Preheat a large, nonstick skillet.
Over medium heat, brown chicken lightly on both sides.
Add onion and cook 3 minutes longer or until onion is soft.
Add mushrooms and tomato sauce; cover and simmer over low heat until chicken is tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in wine and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened.
Place mixture in a greased shallow baking dish and place cheese slices on top.
Bake.

title: florida keys rum-runner
directions: In a blender blend all ingredients except 151 rum at high speed along with one tray of ice cubes until frothy.
Pour into tall glasses and top with a drizzle of 151 rum.

title: texas soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Put all in a large pot (do not drain vegetables) and add taco seasoning and Ranch dressing mix. Stir together and heat at least 30 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush garlic in small bowl; cover with oil.
Refrigerate covered for 30 minutes.
In 1/4 cup garlic oil in medium skillet, fry bread cubes until brown on all sides.
Set aside.
Cook eggs 1 minute in boiling water.
Remove and cool.
In small bowl, combine the lemon juice, Worcestershire, salt, pepper and anchovies and mix well.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Place in large salad bowl.
Drain remaining oil from garlic.
Pour over lettuce and toss to coat evenly.
Break eggs over salad and toss well. Pour on lemon mixture and toss well.
Add bread crumbs and cheeses; toss well.
Serve at once.

title: cranberry punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine juices, ginger ale and frozen berries.
Float thinly sliced orange on top.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Ice cake while it is still warm.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Pour in well-greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 40 to 50 minutes.

title: nanny's casserole
directions: Dice potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain and place in a casserole dish.
Dice ham and cheese and add to potatoes.
Pour in drained peas.
Mix soup and milk and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until casserole becomes thickened.

title: cranberried carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cut diagonally into 1-inch pieces. Cook and drain.
Melt fat and add cranberry sauce.
Cook gently, stirring constantly, until sauce is dissolved.
Add carrots and cook gently for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Do not freeze.

title: english lemon tea squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar. Press into ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2 inch. Build up 1/2 inch edges.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake until no indentation remains when lightly touched in center, about 25 minutes.
Cool, cut into 1 1/2 inch squares. Recipe can be doubled to fit 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: vegetable chili (no oil)
directions: Steam onions, celery, carrots, garlic, green pepper and tomato in 2 tablespoons water instead of oil.
Ground beef can be browned, drained and added, if desired.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken paprika ii
directions: In a pot, brown chicken in Crisco or oleo. Add onion and paprika. Saute until tender. Dissolve bouillon cubes in 3 cups hot water and pour into chicken pot. Boil chicken until tender. Take chicken out of liquid and debone. (Make sure you always have 3 cups of water in your pot; add if necessary.) Bring water back to boiling. Mix flour with approximately 3/4 cup of water. Stir in boiling liquid to make gravy. Add sour cream and deboned chicken.

title: light spinach frittata with tomato salsa
directions: To make the Frittata:
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Heat the oil in a 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add the onion and garlic and cook, stirring, for 3 minutes or until tender. Stir in the spinach.
Reduce the heat to low.
In a large bowl, beat the eggs and egg whites with the milk until light yellow and frothy.
Pour the egg mixture over the spinach in the skillet. Cook for 5 to 7 minutes until the egg mixture is cooked on the bottom and almost set on top.
Sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake in the oven until the eggs are set and the cheese has melted, 5 to 10 minutes.
THIS SERVES 2.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook and stir celery, red pepper and onion in margarine in skillet over medium-high heat until tender.
Reduce heat to low. Add Velveeta process cheese spread.
Stir until melted.
Stir in broccoli and hot sauce; heat thoroughly, stirring constantly. Serve hot with vegetable dippers and crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cmp dessert
directions: Blend flour and oleo like crumbs (will be very rich).
Add nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool thoroughly.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Gently mix together cucumbers, onions, green peppers and salt. Cover with crushed ice and let stand for 3 hours.
Continue to add ice as it melts so cucumbers become crisp and cold.
Drain well.

title: rum sauce
directions: Melt margarine in water over medium heat.
Stir together sugar, flour and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Add vanilla, butter and rum flavorings.
Cook until bubbly.
Poke holes in warm cake and pour over.

title: squash pickles
directions: Boil 2 or 3 minutes; fill jars with squash mixture and liquid. Have tops and rings boiling hot and seal in jars.

title: lamb roast
directions: Place meat on rack in open baking pan; salt and pepper. Insert meat thermometer and roast at 325° until meat reaches a temperature of 175° for medium, 180° for well-done.
After one hour, baste with sauce made with jelly and ketchup.
Baste every half hour.
Total Cooking Time: 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: tossed salad hawaiian
directions: Cut pineapple in half lengthwise through crown.
Remove fruit, leaving shell intact.
Core and cut pineapple into chunks. Combine pineapple, assorted greens, tomatoes, ham and celery; toss lightly.
Spoon salad mixture into pineapple shells.
Serve with dressing.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Roll chicken pieces, boned side up, on cutting board.
Working from center out, pound chicken with a wooden mallet to make cutlets 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: jean mundy's pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add everything else.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Simmer chicken; bone, skin and shred.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add soup, tomatoes and Jack cheese.
Cook slowly until cheese melts.
Add chicken.
Make 2 layers of each ingredient in a 7 x 11-inch pan or 8 x 8-inch pan:
tortillas (overlap), chicken mixture, Cheddar cheese (optional first layer), tortillas, cream chicken and Cheddar cheese.
Top with the Cheddar cheese the last 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour if cold and for 30 minutes if warm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender. Mix well and pour into pie shells. Bake 350° for 30 minutes. Cool, then refrigerate. Serve with whipped cream.

title: shell pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta using the package directions.
Add the broccoli during the last 2 minutes of cooking time; drain well.
Toss the pasta mixture, dressing, ham and cheese in a large bowl.
Chill for 2 hrs.

title: navaho tacos
directions: Brown ground beef and add other ingredients. Cook until done.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Cut broccoli into florets and 1/2 to 1-inch pieces off stem. Slice onion into strips.
Cut carrots diagonally into 1/8-inch thick elliptical slices.
Slice mushrooms 1/8-inch thick.

title: shrimp dill dip
directions: In a bowl, gradually blend together the milk, mayonnaise and lemon juice with the cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add the onion, salt, dill weed and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Stir in the shrimp and chill for 1 hour before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 cups approximately.
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs, blending well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with carrots.
Stir in pecans and pour into greased and floured pan(s).
Bake 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain vegetables, mix with cheese and yogurt.
Place in medium casserole dish that is sprayed with Pam. Combine cracker crumbs with melted margarine.
Sprinkle on top of vegetables.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: geddes gueritas
directions: Put 1 large
tumbler
in freezer.
Remove from freezer. Fill loosely
with
loose
ice.
Return
to
freezer.
Don't measure, but add
tequila
and Triple Sec.
Add fresh straight lime juice to taste
(Note this is the key!
Basically this is a health drink!
Lots of C-rich lime.
I use those Costco-size bottles of "Real
lime".
Don't,
I

repeat do not contaminate with one of those horrible, green slime, Mutant Ninja mixers. This will not only destroy the taste, but compromise the high! This has been tested by reliable sources . . repeatedly.) Half a lime cut
into halves.
Gently squeeze and then "plunk" onto top of health beverage.

title: barbecued chicken sandwiches
directions: Cook chicken until soft.
Debone and chop meat.
Brown onion in butter.
Add chicken and rest of ingredients.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on rolls.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: italian bread
directions: In an extra large bowl, add warm water, yeast and honey.
Wait 10 minutes until yeast foams. Add oil, salt and 3 cups flour.
Mix 5 minutes or until blended.
Add another 2 cups flour gradually until dough forms a ball.
Put flour on board or table.
Put dough on floured board and let it rest for 5 minutes.
Knead until dough is smooth and not sticky.
Add flour as needed to make dough more workable. Put dough into lightly oiled bowl and let rise for 2 hours.
Punch down.
Let rise 1 hour or until doubled in size.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans, mixing well.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Then add raisins and nuts.
Fold in grated zucchini.
Pour 1/2 batter in 2 loaf pans (lightly greased).
Add cocoa and cloves to remaining batter. Pour on top of other batter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Even kids eat this.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 375° until done, 45 minutes to an hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix by hand until smooth.
Add nuts last.
Bake on 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch pan.
In separate bowl, mix flour, sugar and milk well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour fruit on top of flour mixture.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Add all ingredients and simmer until veggies are tender.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and 3/4 cup pecans.
Make 1 or 2 balls.
Roll balls in remaining chopped pecans.
Wrap in wax paper; refrigerate overnight.

title: orange cookies
directions: Combine. Drop on greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Beat cream cheese and American cheese until blended.
Add bacon and onion.
Mound in mushroom caps.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350° (do not overbake).

title: phyl's pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple chunks and juice, cheese, sugar and flour and put into Pyrex baking dish.
Mix butter and Ritz crackers and sprinkle on the pineapple mixture and bake at 350° until done and crackers are toasted.
This is good served with ham or barbecue chicken.

title: jackpot("matt's favorite")
directions: Cook the rotini according to package directions.
Saute the ground beef and onion together.
Drain off excess fat; add salt, chili powder and pepper.
Mix well.
Add soup, water, rotini, kidney beans and half of the cheese; mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mamaw's rhubarb cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut rhubarb into 3/4-inch pieces. Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in a bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
While this is baking, prepare cobbler topping.

title: ribbons of pasta with wild mushrooms and thyme
directions: Brush olive oil in skillet and preheat.
Add mushrooms and shallots and cook until lightly browned.
Add pasta and toss with black pepper to taste.
Garnish with fresh thyme.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix well in bowl.
Pour in a greased and floured cake pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salsa
directions: Simmer ingredients for 1/2 hour to blend flavors.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water; add berries and stir until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour part of mix in dish and let stand in refrigerator.
Spoon sour cream over in a smooth layer.
Pour remaining jello mix over sour cream and let set.

title: 14 day icicle pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in a large container.
Pour boiling water and salt over cucumbers.
Set for 1 week and stir everyday.
Drain water and pour 1 gallon fresh boiling water over cucumbers.
Set 24 hours.
Drain water again.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons alum over cucumbers.
Pour 1 gallon boiling water over cucumbers and let set 24 hours.
Drain water.
Mix 2 quarts vinegar, 6 pints sugar. Bring vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Pour mixture over cucumbers. Set 24 hours.
Lift cucumbers and bring mixture to boil again.
Set 24 hours.
Lift cucumbers.
Pack in jars.
Boil mixture; pour over cucumbers in jars.
Seal

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut pizza dough in half.
Roll out dough.
Layer with pepperoni and cheese to desired thickness. Fold dough over and press to make seam.
Brush with egg white. Bake until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 breads.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix together.
May be served immediately or after refrigeration.

title: vegetable noodle bake
directions: Cook beans and carrots in small amount of boiling, salted water.
Drain and combine any leftover cooking water with milk in white sauce.
Cook noodles.
Add seasonings and cheese to white sauce.
Combine with vegetables and noodles.
Pour into greased shallow baking dish.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: beef and corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in frying pan until done; drain off all fat.
Place in casserole dish; put Tater Tots on top of ground beef and pour can of corn on top.
Pour on cream of celery soup and spread all over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, place the slices of cheese on top and let melt.

title: good veggie bars
directions: Pat crescent rolls onto a jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Italian dressing mix.
Spread on crust.
Top with the chopped veggies.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, sour cream, poppy seed and 1/2 cup grated cheese. Layer chicken in baking dish.
Pour over soup mixture.
Top with remaining 1 1/2 cups cheese and crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on bottom of greased baking dish, then pour in mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top also.
Place baking dish in shallow pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice and water in separate saucepan.
Saute celery, onion and butter in separate saucepan.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Recipe can be doubled and baked in large casserole dish for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and cocoa.
Stir milk in gradually.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Stir in beaten egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Pour in pie crust.
When cooled and ready to eat, top with Cool Whip.

title: karen's brownies
directions: Mix brownie mix as instructed on box.
Pour half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix cream cheese and butter with remaining ingredients.
Pour cream cheese mixture over brownie mixture.
Add remaining brownie mixture on top and swirl with a knife to marble.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with Duncan Hines chocolate frosting.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream the Crisco, margarine and cream cheese.
Add vanilla and salt.
Gradually add 10x sugar and milk.
Beat well at high speed. Makes enough for 1 cake.

title: persimmon custard pie
directions: Roll out pastry or press out whole wheat pastry to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Flute edges.
With a mixer, beat eggs.
Add persimmon, sugar, salt, spices and milk.
Blend thoroughly and pour into pastry shell.
Bake on the lowest rack of a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking until pie looks set but jiggles slightly in center when pan is shaken, about 45 minutes more.
Cool to room temperature to serve. Top with whipped cream.
This tastes much like a pumpkin pie.

title: chicken and wild rice bake(microwave)
directions: Combine rice mix, seasonings from packet, soup, milk and celery in 4-quart casserole.
Arrange chicken over top of rice mix.
Cook, covered, on full power for 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is done and rice is tender.
Yield: 6 servings.
tags: quick-cooking long grain and wild rice mix

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package until tender, but not soft.
Chop pimento, onion and cheese.
Combine all ingredients while macaroni is hot.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
This may be prepared in advance and refrigerated or frozen until ready to cook.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all, except vanilla, butter and nuts.
Bring to boil and cook until forms a soft ball, stirring frequently.
Take from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Beat until cool and thick enough to drop.
Add chopped nuts and drop by teaspoon onto buttered waxed paper or pour into a buttered pie pan.

title: pecan pie surprise bar
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup dry cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix with butter and one of the eggs.
Mix until crumbly.
Press crumb mixture into a well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes until light golden brown.
Combine the reserved cake mix with remaining eggs, brown sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed 1 or 2 minutes.
Pour over crust. Sprinkle with pecans.
Return to oven and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool and cut in bars.
Makes 36.

title: c f's
directions: Place peanut butter chips on top of milk chocolate chips in a large glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Mix ingredients in a bowl and add peanuts.
Blend by hand until smooth.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 more minutes. Mix again and then spoon onto wax paper.
Put into refrigerator until hard.
Enjoy.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Layer broccoli, ham and cheese in 2 to 3-quart dish.
Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Pour over layers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish; set aside. Combine peaches, sugar and cinnamon and set aside.

title: sour cream lasagne
directions: Brown the onions, garlic and meat.
Drain off the fat.
Add the tomato sauce and water and simmer 20 minutes uncovered (add spices - basil, oregano etc. if desired).

title: fruit salad pie
directions: Make 2 (10-inch) pie crusts.
Put on to heat the cherries, pineapple and 1 cup sugar.
Cook until fairly thick.
Remove from heat; add jello.
Let cool.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Pour in pie crusts.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: fried green tomatoes, cucumbers too
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes.
Mix flour and meal.
Put oil in frying pan; heat.
Put tomatoes in meal/flour mixture.
Cover both sides.
Put in oil.
Fry about 3 minutes; turn over.
Add hot peppers.
Cover; finish frying until done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch and water 1 minute, stirring while cooking.
Add the egg yolks; boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with desired topping.

title: cheese crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: helen's copper pennies
directions: Cream butter.
Add ingredients and mix well.
Form into small balls.
Mash tops with a fork.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes mauna kea
directions: Mix everything except coconut and paprika.
Put in a buttered casserole.
Bake covered 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove cover, top with coconut and paprika.
Brown quickly under broiler before serving.
This may be varied by layering with banana slices.

title: caramel peanut butter dip
directions: Microwave caramels and water on high for 1 minute; stir. Microwave 1 minute more or until smooth.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Microwave for 30 seconds or until smooth.
Serve warm with apple wedges.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer vegetables; spread mayonnaise on top and sprinkle with sugar, cheese and bacon.
Refrigerate 24 hours covered with Saran Wrap.

title: pineapple orange cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat 2 minutes on high, then 1 minute on medium.
Pour into 3 greased and floured round cake pans (8-inch) or 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer first five ingredients in big pot for 1 hour.
Save broth when completed.
In bottom of casserole dish mix and place diced cooked chicken, cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup broth.
On top of this mix and place stuffing mix, butter, onion and 1 cup broth.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: red cake
directions: Mix together vinegar and soda; set aside.
Beat together butter and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Break apart with spatula while still warm. Cream together the next three items and sprinkle on top of pretzels.
Cover with 1 can pineapple pie filling or fruit of your choice.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix next 3 ingredients and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ecto cherry cheer punch
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in the can of frozen pineapple juice.
Add the Hi-C cherry, Hi-C Ecto Cooler and Sprite.
Blend in ice cream until thick.
Serves 25.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients, except paprika, and pour over chicken. Sprinkle generously with paprika. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until tender. Serve with hot, fluffy rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sherried fruit
directions: Melt butter and mix in brown sugar and flour; add sherry. Cook until thickened and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake 30 minutes at 350° (in advance).
Serve at room temperature.

title: condensed milk doughnuts
directions: Mix all of these ingredients together and depending on which kind of flour you use, you may want to add another 1/2 to 1 cup so the dough can be handled easily.
Roll out and cut with doughnut cutter and fry in deep fat at 375° until lightly brown on one side and turn carefully to brown on other side.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
May tip in sugar as these are not a very sweet item.

title: hot mexican-style spinach dip
directions: Heat oil in heavy medium skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and saute until softened, stirring occasionally, about 4 minutes. Add tomatoes and chilies and cook 2 minutes.
Transfer mixture to large bowl and stir in spinach, Monterey Jack cheese, cream cheese, half and half, olives and vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into shallow ovenproof baking dish.
(Can be prepared 2 days ahead.)
Cover and refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake until dip is bubbly and top is light brown, about 35 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: kentucky slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot and set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients and mix well.
Add cabbage and carrots and mix well. Chill before serving.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg, mixing well. Add salad oil, vanilla, flour, soda, salt and other ingredients, mixing well.
Form balls the size of small walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in water. Bake 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Have eggs and butter at room temperature.
Cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar and whip until fluffy.
Beat eggs one at a time into mixture; mix well.
Place all dry ingredients into sifter.
Sift into creamy mixture and add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour and five minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix pineapple, onions, brown sugar and tomato sauce together and pour over chicken pieces.
Bake at 375° until done, about 45 minutes.
Turn once to brown both sides.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Marinate beef in wine for 30 minutes or longer.
Heat wok or heavy skillet.
Add oil and heat thoroughly.
Stir fry garlic and ginger until light golden brown.
Remove beef from marinade and stir fry for 4 minutes.
Add vegetables and continue to stir fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in soy sauce.
Add soy sauce mixture and marinade.
Stir fry stirring constantly another minute.
Serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, drain and put layer of meat mixture in baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup with the browned ground beef, before putting the first layer of meat in the baking dish.
Top with a layer of grated cheese on top of the first layer of meat. Then add a layer of Tater Tots.
Repeat the procedures, ending with Tater Tots on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: caribbean banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Blend together eggs, bananas, milk, butter and rum extract.
Add all at once to flour mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: spicy harvest bread
directions: Sift whole wheat flour with next 5 ingredients into bowl. Beat egg whites, sugar, honey and oil in large bowl.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons hot water.
Mix well.
Stir in shredded carrot and yam.
Add dry ingredients and raisins.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured 2 pound coffee can.
Place in crock-pot. Cover with damp paper towel and cook, partially covered, on high for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: family fun fill-ups
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and stir in flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, nut, dates and morsels. Add Rice Krispies.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls, about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen cookies.

title: taco salad(mexican hat salad)
directions: Brown pepper, hamburger and onion; drain off grease. In large pot, combine chili beans, taco seasoning and stewed tomatoes. Add hamburger mixture. Simmer for about 30 minutes. Cut up tomatoes and lettuce. Shred cheese. Put Doritos or corn chips in plate; put hamburger on Doritos, then layer with tomatoes, cheese, lettuce and sour cream.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl or blender; mix well. Pour mixture into pie crust.
Recipe will fill 2 regular size pies or 1 deep dish pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown or test with toothpick for firmness in center of pie.

title: apple cake
directions: Soak diced apples in apple juice.
Soak raisins in cranberry juice.
Set both aside.
Beat eggs, sugar and vegetable oil.
Add vanilla, flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Combine nuts, apples and raisins with all above.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Can use 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.
Grease pan.
Bake cupcakes for 40 minutes.
Makes 36 cupcakes.

title: sweet and sour kielbasi
directions: Boil kielbasi for 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°, covered for 1/2 hour and uncovered for 1 hour.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Fill churn up with milk.
Add 2 more cups sugar if fruit is unsweetened.

title: diet tuna loaf(tastes like salmon loaf)
directions: Drain tuna, reserving 2 tablespoons of liquid.
In bowl, combine with egg and Wasa.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Add onion and pepper to liquid; mix.
Flake tuna in bowl and stir.
Spray small loaf pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: frosty
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor. Blend on medium speed, stopping to stir several times with a long spoon if necessary to help the ingredients blend well.

title: spiced tea(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Put cloves and cinnamon in bag; add to other ingredients. Let mixture stand until flavor is mellowed, then remove bag with spices. Best when served hot.

title: mexican style hot potatoes
directions: Cube or slice potatoes.
Cut onion and bell pepper into 1/2 inch strips.
Chop hot peppers finely.
Combine potatoes with other ingredients.
Melt margarine; stir into mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Dish is done when potatoes begin to brown throughout.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: two cheese chicken enchiladas
directions: heat oven to 350 degrees.
In saucepan, combine chicken, 1/2 c. of the Pace, and cream cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese is melted.
Stir in onions.
Spoon about 1/3 c. chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up and place seam side down in 8X12 inch baking dish.
Combine velveeta and 1/2 cup pace in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese is melted.
Pour evenly over tortillas. Cover with foil.
Bake 25 minutes.
Heat remaining 1/2 cup Pace; spoon down center of enchiladas.
Top as desired with additional Pace picante sauce.
makes 4 servings.

title: oyster filling
directions: In a casserole bowl, crush crackers about 1/2 high.
Place butter pats, then oysters and milk.
Repeat layering.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Peel potatoes and slice them into 1/4-inch sticks and arrange them over bottom of flat baking dish.
Pour orange juice over this.
Mix molasses and pineapple.
Put chicken over orange juice. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with pineapple mixture. Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Top with cheese and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 4 people.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter and Crisco; add sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and flour, start and end with flour.
Bake in a greased tube pan with a lid.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mopping sauce
directions: Best when used on pork ribs around a campfire.

title: apples and sweet potatoes in orange glaze
directions: Wash potatoes and cook in boiling water until tender.
Peel and core apples.
Slice. Peel potatoes.
Cut in halves and arrange both potatoes and apples in baking dish.

title: beef with tater tots
directions: Put ground chuck in bottom of large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with onions.
Spread cream of chicken soup over ground chuck, then Cheddar cheese soup.
Top with as many Tater Tots as you can. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix above ingredients well and bake at 325° in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours. Pour filling over cake.

title: party pecans
directions: Beat egg white stiff.
Mix with water.
Dip pecans into egg white and water mix.
Dip pecans into mix of sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage or bacon.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt and mustard.
Arrange bread cubes in bottom of 9 X 13 baking dish and top with sausage or bacon.	Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-45 minutes.

title: fried baked pies
directions: Roll 1 biscuit on floured board to the size of a saucer.
Put enough pie filling to fill rolled out dough.
Wet around edge of dough with water.
Fold together and seal with a fork.

title: rice krispy treats
directions: Stir all together in pan on low heat.
When it melts together, pour into greased dish. Slice into squares when cool.

title: texas style chili
directions: Cook beef, sausage, onion and garlic in Dutch oven; drain. Add next 6 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add beans and simmer 20 more minutes.

title: mandarin chicken
directions: Rinse the chicken and pat dry.
Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper in a sturdy bag.
Put chicken in bag and shake to coat. Heat about 1/2-inch oil in a heavy frying pan.
Brown chicken on both sides, frying about 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle chicken with cloves and nutmeg.
Add 1 tablespoon water to the pan and cover, cooking over low heat another 20 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl and stir well. Shape mixture into 42 (1-inch) meatballs.
Arrange meatballs on rack of a broiler pan, coated with cooking spray.
Broil 5 1/2-inches from heat for 10 minutes or until browned, turning frequently.

title: oven stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a Dutch oven, layer vegetables and meat, omitting peas.
Pour tomato soup over all.
Add bay leaf, salt, pepper and tapioca.
Pour water over all.
Seal Dutch oven with aluminum foil and the lid.
Place in oven for 6 to 10 hours, no peeking.
Remove from oven and stir in can of peas.
Good with fresh French bread or biscuits and a salad.
Serves 8.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Add all ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: aunt stella's applesauce cake
directions: This is a very old recipe.
No instructions were given.
Blend all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour. Top with Brown Sugar Icing.

title: apple bean bake
directions: In a skillet, melt butter; add cubed apples and cook until tender.
Add brown and white sugar; stir and cook until sugar is melted.
Stir in cinnamon, catsup and molasses.
Add beans and mix well.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream walnuts
directions: Cook sugar and sour cream to 240° (candy thermometer) and pour over nuts which are placed on wax paper.
When mixture hardens, break up nut pieces.
A great holiday addition.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 cups boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and 8 quarts of water (2 gallons).
May be frozen.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Mix Cool Whip in pudding.
Layer crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pudding, then another layer of crackers.
Continue until all pudding is used.
End with a layer of crackers.
Place in freezer for 2 hours.
Cover with cake frosting.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Note:
Can add 1 can crabmeat if desired.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Spread refried beans in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Next spread sour cream over beans.
Pour sauce over sour cream, then layer onions, tomatoes and then cheese.
Top with black olives.
Place a spoonful on each chip or dip out with chips.

title: chili
directions: In 4-quart pan over medium heat, cook meat, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned and vegetables are tender. Pour off fat.

title: grilled chicken marinade
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Place chicken in Ziploc bag; pour marinade over.
Place in refrigerator overnight or for at least 12 hours.
Grill chicken for 1 hour (or until done).
Turn and baste chicken with remaining marinade.

title: camp biscuits
directions: Stir flour, milk, baking powder, salt and sugar together.
Cut in shortening until mix looks like corn meal.
Store in
airtight containers.
To
make biscuits add water to make dough; roll out. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Three cups mix plus	3/4 cup of water equals 1 1/2 dozen biscuits.	Whole mix equals biscuits for 100.

title: elephant stew
directions: Dice the elephant into small pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover; season.
Cook over kerosene stoves about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but only if necessary, because most people do not like to find hares in their stew.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti. Brown hamburger and add sauce. Mix together. Put 1/2 of the spaghetti in dish. Add 1 can of soup and 1/2 of the cheese. Put rest of spaghetti and other can of soup; top with rest of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts and turns lightly brown.

title: country cheese snacks
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, cheeses and green onions. Spread on bread; place on a baking sheet.
Broil 4 inches from the heat until golden and bubbly, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Garnish with parsley and olives.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
2 cups spread.

title: eagle brand substitute
directions: Add the dry milk to warm water and mix well.
Place in a pan of hot water and stir in sugar until dissolved.
Store in refrigerator.
Equal to 1 can Eagle Brand milk.

title: rice krispie squares
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows together, stirring often.
Can be done in microwave.
Immediately add Rice Krispies and toss until well coated.
Nuts or chocolate chips can be added.
Press with spatula into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and cool.
Cut into squares (about 2 dozen).
A quick and delightful dessert.

title: sweet tomato chutney
directions: Put the garlic, ginger and 1/2 cup wine vinegar into the container of an electric blender and blend at high speed until smooth. In a 4-quart heavy-bottomed pot with nonmetallic finish, place the tomatoes and juice from the can, the rest of the wine vinegar, sugar, salt and cayenne pepper in pot. Bring to a boil. Add puree from blender. Lower heat and simmer gently, uncovered, for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until chutney becomes thick. Chutney should cling to spoon. Stir occasionally at first and more frequently later as it thickens. You may need to lower the heat as the liquid diminishes. You should end up with about 2 1/2 cups chutney and it should be at least as thick as honey after it cools. Add almonds and raisins. Simmer, stirring about 5 minutes. Turn heat off and allow to cool. Bottle and keep refrigerated.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Spread softened ice cream evenly in bottom of crust.
Freeze until ice cream is firm.
Spread caramel sauce over ice cream. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cover with whipped chocolate topping.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add onion, cheese, mayonnaise, mushroom soup and egg.
Top with crumbled cheese crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.
If browning too fast, cover with foil.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Heat butter in large 3-quart saucepan.
Cook okra, onions and green pepper until soft.
Add broth, tomatoes with liquid, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in chicken and heat through.
Stir in parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: hawaiian tea
directions: Combine juice and spices in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 1 minute.
Add tea bags.
Cover and steep 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove tea bags and spices.
Sweeten with brown sugar if desired.
Garnish with cinnamon sticks if desired.

title: pot of beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cut up onions and bacon or ham hock. Combine pinto beans, onion, bacon or ham hock, garlic salt and chili powder.
Cook.
Two hours later add 1 teaspoon more of chili powder and tomato paste.
Cook 2 hours.
After 2 hours, add salt and pepper (to cover top), cumin and oregano.
Then cook and eat. Cook on low.
Start on high and then after it boils, keep adding water.

title: mary beth's cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into 1-inch chunks and cook in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Cook bacon until brown; remove from pan and drain on paper towel.
Saute diced onions and peppers in bacon drippings until tender.
Mix all ingredients and put into casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°
until browned, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown the ground beef; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add a handful of noodles or macaroni and cook for 10 more minutes.
Season with garlic salt, onion salt or seasoned salt.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water in a double boiler until thick and smooth.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a baked pastry shell and chill.
Serve with whipped cream or frozen topping.

title: cajun rice
directions: Saute onion in oil. Stir in chicken broth, green pepper, chili powder, thyme, paprika and cayenne pepper. Mix well.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, butter, baking powder and salt together. Pour into a greased baking dish.
Mix peaches and 1 cup sugar together and pour on top of batter.
Pour 1/2 cup boiling water over fruit and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on English muffins.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Place on cookie sheet.
Broil 8 minutes or until brown.

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Thaw and drain raspberries.
Drain pineapple.
Reserve juices. Add thawed orange juice to drained juice; this would measure 2 1/2 cups.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add juices and chill until partially set.
Add the raspberries and pineapple.
Put the mixture in 1 1/2 to 2-quart mold and chill until set.
This is a nice Christmas salad.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in a greased baking dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter or oleo (optional) and bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Wash and skin chicken.
Roll in butter and then in Rice Krispies and place in a baking dish.
Pour milk alongside chicken.
Cover dish lightly with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then uncover and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: modern beef pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Layer in dish the meat, vegetables, potatoes and then top with biscuits.
Place in a 350° oven until biscuits are done.
Top with cheese.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Saute half the onion and 2 red peppers in olive oil.
Heat can of beans.
Add hot sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook rice.
Add sauteed onion and peppers to beans.
Bring to boil; cover and turn off heat.
Serve beans over rice.
Sprinkle with remaining onion, celery and additional hot sauce.
Can be served as a main or side dish.

title: gourmet pork
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat chops and brown on both sides. Place in baking dish.
Combine soup, water, ginger and rosemary; pour over chops; sprinkle with 1/2 of the onions.
Cover and bake until chops are tender.
Uncover; sprinkle with the balance of onions and bake 10 minutes.
Remove chops; add sour cream to the gravy.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and canning salt together and let sit at room temperature for two hours. Do not add water. Drain and rinse out salt. Add remaining ingredients and stir. Store in refrigerator. Best flavor if you wait a couple of weeks before serving.

title: jenna's "somewhere over the rainbow cookies"
directions: With electric beater, mix eggs, sugar and flour.
Pour in melted butter and almond extract; mix well.
Separate the batter into 3 dishes.
Add green food coloring to one, red coloring to the second and yellow to the third.
Stir each color well.
Grease and flour 3 (10 x 6-inch) pans.
Pour mixtures into each pan equally and spread with a spoon.
Bake on top rack for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Let cool, then remove cakes from pans and place one layer on a flat surface (either a cutting board or a cookie sheet).

title: georgia special orange cream cake
directions: Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First:
Mix together flour, pecans and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly browned (let cool).

title: banana nut cake
directions: Bake at 350° about 45 minutes for oblong, 35 minutes for layers.

title: gingerbread
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Bake in a 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch greased pan, in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill before serving.
Good with bread or vegetables.

title: chicken-cranberry bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken breasts into 2 or 3 pieces.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour dressing and cranberries over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato broccoli soup
directions: In large pot, saut garlic and onion in oil for a few minutes. Add potatoes, broth, salt and pepper to the pot. Bring to a boil and simmer until potatoes are tender. While potatoes are cooking, prepare the broccoli. Wash and cut up, then steam or microwave until tender. When potatoes are tender, mash them up in the pot. Stir in the broccoli and half and half. Cook on low another 10 minutes. Leftovers will be very thick. You may wish to add more liquid.

title: no chop vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients into a crock pot.
Bring to a boil on high heat; then turn to low heat and simmer for seven to eight hours.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frying pan.
Add soup and mix well.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Alternate layers of potatoes and meat mixture.
Add milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done.

title: chocolate-peanut butter swirls
directions: Mix the peanut butter, powdered sugar, coconut and corn syrup in a medium bowl.
Stir in cereal.
Shape mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls; flatten slightly.
Heat chocolate chips and water in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until melted. Cool.
Dip top of balls into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper lined cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm, about 30 minutes. Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix prepared pudding mix with condensed milk.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip.
In a bowl, place 1 layer of wafers and cover with bananas. Pour on pudding mixture.
Alternate layers until all the mix is used.
Top with the rest of Cool Whip and chill.

title: vanilla wafer-coconut pound cake(from the files of dessie bell hayes)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Fold in vanilla wafers, coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Bake at 325° in Bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Add egg and milk; mix well. Spread in an 8-inch square pan coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut into 18 pieces. Top 9 pieces with half of the strawberries. Stack the other 9 on top of the first. Top with berries and a dollop of Cool Whip. Serves 9.

title: brown meatballs
directions: Roll hamburger into meatballs.
Fry until done.
Heat gravy mix.
Serve with rice on platter, then your meatballs and top with gravy.

title: lemon pie supreme
directions: Bring to boil sugar
and
cups water.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/3 cup water.
Add
to syrup, cook until clear. Beat egg yolks, add lemon
juice and lemon rind.
Add to syrup mixture; cook until thick.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Do not add additional salt!!!
Cook broccoli and drain. Combine eggs, soup, mayonnaise and onion.
Mix these with broccoli and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Melt butter and mix with croutons.
Spread croutons over top of broccoli mixture.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.
Very good for freezing.
Leftovers are excellent!

title: quick quiche
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly and blend in the rest of the ingredients. Ham, bacon or green chilies may be used in this mixture.
Melt 1/2 cup of margarine or butter.
Pour half into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and other half into the mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot set on a low temperature.
Cook 20 to 24 hours.
These beans are usually juicier, forming what is called a "liquor".
Beans usually soak up the juice when refrigerated.
May be frozen.
Reheat slowly.

title: corn pudding
directions: Pour corn in baking dish.
Add sugar and eggs.
Put cornstarch in milk.
Add this to the mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into ice cream freezer and fill with milk to the fill line on freezer.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes.
Mix cheese and eggs together and add to zucchini mixture.
Add remaining ingredients, except for mustard.
Brush mustard over pie crusts.
Pour mixture into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel and slice onions.
In a skillet, saute onions in butter over low heat until soft and slightly brown.
Sprinkle with flour. Add water, stirring.
Crumble bouillon cubes and add to pan.
Add bouquet garni, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook for about 20 minutes.
Add white wine to soup.
Transfer soup to individual ovenproof large bowl.
Place sliced bread on top. Sprinkle generously with grated cheese.
Add bread and cheese when reheating.
Ten minutes boiling time, 50 minutes total.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add hot water.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to sugar-yolk mixture. Beat well.
Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tabulah - crushed wheat salad
directions: Cover burghul with cold water and soak 1/2 hour.
Drain and squeeze dry in dampened cloth.
Place in large bowl and add all ingredients except oil.
When thoroughly mixed, slowly add the oil, continuing to mix.
Place on platter on bed of lettuce leaves and garnish with sliced black olives.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.
Best made one day before serving.

title: yams hawaiian
directions: Place yams in buttered 1-quart casserole.
Arrange banana on top.
Pour juice over all.
Sprinkle with salt.
Top with pecans and coconut.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll into balls and place on greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: creamy macaroni and cheese
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil in a large Dutch oven; stir in macaroni.
Return to a rapid boil and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Combine macaroni and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Garnish, if desired.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add both together and stir carefully.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean from center.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes and then cool on rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: alma's dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, spread with crushed pineapple.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup milk and salt and beat until fluffy, then add pudding mix and 2 cups milk and mix well.
Spread mixture over pineapple.
Then spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all together and cook to 290° or hard-crack stage.
Pour over 1 1/2 gallons of popped, salted corn.
Mix thoroughly and turn out on table to dry for 1 1/2 hours or can be formed into popcorn balls.

title: jezebel on the mountain(hot pineapple sauce)
directions: Mix together and pour over an 8 ounce block of cream cheese. Best to let marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Best with club crackers and great as a dip for fried chicken.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Combine shortening with brown sugar, spices and salt until light and fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; blend.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to sugar mixture; stir until well blended.
Cover and chill.
Roll out 1/4 of dough at a time on lightly floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with gingerbread man cutter.
Transfer to greased cookie sheet.
Before baking, press currants for eyes and nose.
M&M's are popular for the buttons and slivers of candied cherries for mouth, belt and shoes.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes, or until done.
Cool on racks. Makes about 15 men.

title: holiday frost
directions: In a microwavable mug, add all of the ingredients.
Cook in microwave 1 minute (warm), 1 1/2 minutes (hot) on High.
Take out and cool for 1 minute.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Serve.
Serves 1.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Wash
strawberries and drain.
Slice if desired.
Bake 2 pie shells
and
cool.
Mix
water, sugar, cornstarch and salt until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add box of Jell-O. Add additional
red
food coloring if desired.
When cool, add fresh berries
and pour into pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: sally turo's zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt Crisco.
Add first 4 ingredients. Add egg; mix.
Gradually add remaining ingredients.
Place in bread pan and bake 60 to 65 minutes or until done.

title: pralines
directions: Boil syrup, sugar, milk, corn syrup and water until it forms a soft ball when dropped in water. Move from heat and add butter; stir until melted. After it cools, add vanilla and beat until creamy. Add pecans. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour pork and beans into a 1-quart lightly greased baking dish. Mix in onions, brown sugar, molasses, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard. Top mixture with bacon strips and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon bread twists
directions: Roll out bread into oblong, 24 x 6-inches.
Spread with soft butter.
Sprinkle half of dough with mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Fold other half over.
Cut into 24 strips, 1-inch wide. Hold strip at one end and twist in opposite directions.
Place on greased baking sheet, 2 inches apart.
Press both ends of twist to baking sheet.
(For buttery taste, grease sheet with butter flavor shortening.)
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: miracle fudge frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Place over simmering water; blend ingredients until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Cool, stirring frequently, until frosting reaches desired spreading consistency.
Yield: Frosting for two 9-inch round layers or one 9 x 13-inch loaf.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg in a saucepan; cook and stir just until apples are softened.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, cream shortening, butter and brown sugar.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Pat half of flour mixture in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Spread apples over top, then crumble remaining flour mixture over apples.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream if desired.

title: "some" chicken
directions: Place chicken in a pan, side by side.
Mix the Russian dressing, soup mix and cranberry sauce or jam.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serve over rice.
If doubling for a large group, cook about 10 extra minutes.

title: salmon saute
