directions: Heat nonstick skillet with the oil.
Put fillets in when hot. Saute 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
In the last minute of cooking, squeeze the lemon over fillets and toss in the capers.
Makes 2 servings.

title: manly oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Drop golf ball size portions onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen large cookies.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set aside until cool.
Cook juice from pineapple and oranges with sugar, flour, eggs and salt until smooth and thick.
Pour over fruit and macaroni.
Cool 4 hours and overnight.
Then mix in Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: apple pinwheel
directions: Mix sugar, water and margarine in a saucepan and simmer.
Roll biscuit dough to a rectangle as for a jelly roll.
Peel apples and grate or chop.
Cover dough with apples and roll.
Cut into 1-inch pieces and put in 15 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour sauce over apple pinwheels and bake until golden brown in 350° oven.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to batter alternately with milk.
Mask 1/2 cup blueberries; stir into batter.
Add remaining blueberries.
Place into muffin papers; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: venison tenders
directions: Use only lean venison, cut into 1-inch cubes.
Slice mushrooms.
Pour contents in crock-pot.
Cook on low 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 4.
Serve over rice or noodles with fresh sourdough bread.

title: strawberry danish
directions: Crumble angel food cake in large bowl and mix in 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Press the mixture into a 9 x 13 inch pan and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. After mixing thoroughly, add remaining Cool Whip and mix well. Spread mixture on top of cake mixture.
In another bowl, combine the strawberries and glace.
Pour the strawberry mixture over the cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: hershey chocolate cake
directions: Mix, bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: corn relish
directions: Remove seeds from pepper and finely chop. Comb. corn, pepper,mustard, and mayonnaise together in medium bowl, and mix well.
Spoon corn relish into screw-top jar and serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: aunt ruth's easy chicken breast
directions: Wrap asparagus spear in half ham slice; wrap chicken over ham making a roll.
Arrange rolls in 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Pour undiluted soup over the rolls.
Sprinkle button mushrooms over top. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Remove cover and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix all ingredients and store in a glass jar with a lid.
Let stand at room temperature for 3 weeks.
Stir 2 times a week.
Serve over ice cream or cake.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine nuts, syrup and milk.
Pour into uncooked pie shells. Cook in preheated oven at 350° until done (top will start to crack).
Makes 2 pies.

title: chex mix
directions: Melt together the margarine, garlic powder, onion salt, poultry seasoning and salt.

title: corn bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk mixture, beaten eggs, flour and corn meal.
Beat until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Batter will be stiff.
Turn into 2 greased 8-inch round cake pans or 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: breakfast or brunch gargage
directions: Combine eggs and 1/2 cup cheese; set aside.
In medium hot skillet, cook potatoes, ham and onion in hot oil for about 8 minutes or until potatoes and onions are tender.
Add the egg mixture to potatoes and
ham/sausage.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are cooked but still glossy and moist. Transfer to serving plate and top with remaining cheese.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.
You can double recipe.

title: pressure cooked pork chow mein
directions: Brown pork in a small amount of oil in pressure cooker. Add celery and onion and fill cooker about halfway with water, then add soy sauce and seasonings.
Cook at full pressure for about
15 to 20 minutes, then add bean sprouts and vegetables. Add
more water
and soy sauce to taste, if desired.
Thicken with
a
flour and water mixture.
Serve over rice.
Top with crispy chow mein noodles.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook and stir celery, red pepper and onion in butter in skillet over medium-high heat until tender.
Reduce heat to low. Add Velveeta; stir until melted.
Stir in broccoli and hot sauce. Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Serve hot with veggies or crackers.
Yields approximately 4 cups.

title: hot virginia dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Place in chafing dish or casserole dish, and top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix above ingredients and press on a cookie sheet about 1/2 or 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into squares and freeze.
When ready to use, dip squares in flour and brown.
Lay in long pan, mix 1 can golden mushroom soup and 1 can onion soup.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, then at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Reserve 1 cup of broth.
Bone when cool and cut in bite size pieces.
Crush Doritos.
Dilute chicken soup with broth from boiled chicken.
Add Ro-Tel and chicken.
Mix together.
Layer crushed Doritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/3 of the bag for the top.
Add chicken mixture.
Cube cheese and melt in microwave oven.
Pour on top of chicken mixture. Sprinkle crushed Doritos on top of cheese.
Bake in 325° oven until cheese bubbles through top of Doritos.

title: chinese chop suey
directions: In a frying pan, place first 6 items in pan.
Add enough hot water to mushroom juice to make 1 cup.
Cover and cook 10 minutes. Add bean sprouts and cook well.
Bring to a boil.
In small cup, mix cold water, cornstarch, soy sauce and sugar.
Add to frying pan and cook 5 minutes.
Push vegetables to sides of pan.
Place meat in middle of pan and cover with vegetables.
Cook 3 minutes or until meat is done.
Be careful not to overcook shrimp, if used. Stir to mix.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pork chops and rice bake
directions: Season chops and brown on both sides in skillet with melted margarine.
Spread uncooked rice in casserole dish.
Mix soup, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Pour over rice, adding water if needed to cover rice.
Place chops on top and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until rice is tender. Additional water may be added to get rice tender.

title: miss pearl's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use teaspoon more baking powder with sweet milk and pinch of soda. Especially good cooked in an iron skillet on the top of the stove.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Mix sour cream and butter; gradually add flour.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Put in muffin pan.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° until brown (about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: maple-pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; refrigerate until ready to fill.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly with rotary beater.
Add sugar, flour, syrup and butter; beat until well blended.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Turn into unbaked pie shell; bake at 40 to 45 minutes or just until filling is set in center. (Shake pie gently; center should be firm.)
Let cool on wire rack. If desired, serve garnished with whipped cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2 -inch cubes.
Layer ingredients in the order listed in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in 300° oven for 4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: fluffy baked omelet(unusual; delicious; easy)
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until very thick and lemon-colored. Beat whites until frothy; add water and salt and beat until stiff, but not dry.
Fold yolks into whites very gently.
Fold in cheese and any optional ingredients.
Bake in hot (preheated) buttered 10 to 12-inch skillet at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden.
(Done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.) Serves 2 to 4.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O
in one cup boiling water.
Add one cup juice drained from pineapple.
If not quite 1 cup add a little water to make
a
cup.
Add crushed pineapple and chill until thickened. Then
add cheese, oranges and marshmallows.
Last, fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mash potatoes in a large bowl. Combine potatoes with egg yolks, milk, butter, vanilla, salt and spices. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into the sweet potato mixture. When blended, gently pour into a pie shell. Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Pie is done when knife is inserted into center of pie and comes out clean. Let cool. Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.

title: sue lindstedt's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to butter mixture.
Mix in nuts and chocolate bits.
Make a ball with one large tablespoon of dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crispix candy
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients.
Pour half of mixture over 1/2 box of Crispix cereal.
Place in a bag with powdered sugar. Shake gently until coated.
Spread out to cool.
Repeat with other half.

title: zesty sausage squares
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pat down.
Saute sausage and onions; drain on paper towels, then spread on Bisquick mixture.
Beat egg with remaining mayonnaise,
Cheddar cheese and green chilies.
Spread on top of meat layer.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Pour all ingredients into crock-pot and simmer about 8 hours on low.

title: cabbage burger bake
directions: Spread 1/2 of cabbage in a large buttered casserole.
Saute bacon strips; drain and set aside.
Brown onion and uncooked rice.
Spoon onion/rice over cabbage.
Brown hamburger; spoon over rice.
Season to taste.
Top with remaining cabbage.
Heat spaghetti sauce and water; pour over cabbage so it seeps in.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, covered, until rice is tender, then uncovered until bacon is crisp.

title: pastry shells
directions: Let cheese and oleo stand until room temperature.
Add flour and cream together.
Chill one hour.
Pinch off small balls and press in miniature muffin pans.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 24 shells.

title: pumpkin gingerbread
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, sugar and orange peel.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg whites; beat well.
Mix in pumpkin, corn syrup and molasses until smooth.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together the red food coloring and instant cocoa and set aside.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs and coloring paste.
Beat 10 minutes. Add the buttermilk and slowly add the flour, salt and vanilla.
Remove from mixer.
Lightly fold in 1 tablespoon vinegar and soda mixed together. Don't beat!
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter and flour (take out 2 tablespoons flour to mix with the fruit and nuts to keep from sticking together).
Add spices.
Mix fruit and nuts with 2 tablespoons flour and add to other ingredients, mixing together.
Chill 1 hour.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 250°.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup; cook over low heat. Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved; cool.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix.
Pour filling into pastry shell and top with pecan halves.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Take chopped meat and season to taste.
(Suggestion:
Add 1 egg and 1/2 cup ketchup, not from the bottle mentioned, 1/4 to 1/2 cup oatmeal to bind, salt, pepper and herb seasoning.)
Form meatballs about one inch in diameter.

title: country thumb cookies
directions: Cream first five ingredients.
Gradually stir in flour, blending well.
Cover and chill until firm enough to handle. Work 1/2 at a time.
Keep rest in refrigerator.
Shape into nickel size balls and roll in nuts.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Gently press thumb into center and fill indentation with jelly or preserves.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (until brown). Store in refrigerator in tins.

title: spice tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in a tightly sealed jar.

title: parsley baked chicken
directions: *Two each: breasts, thighs and legs will serve 4 people.

title: hot wine cranberry punch(serves 6 to 8 mugs or 10 to 12 punch cups)
directions: Combine ingredients in slow-cooking pot.
Heat on low for 1 to 2 hours (in crock-pot).
Strain and serve hot.
May be kept hot and served from crock-pot set on the lowest setting.

title: dill sauce(california shrimp cocktail)
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Serve with shrimp.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chili
directions: Simmer all ingredients together for about an hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar well.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg. Add flour, one-half cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spoon into well-greased 10-inch tube pan dusted with flour.
Put in cold oven and bake at 275° for about 1 1/2 hours or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: nepalese potatoes
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in large skillet. Add potatoes and fry until golden brown on all sides. Remove potatoes. Melt remaining butter; saute onions. Stir in spices, water and salt. Cook about 3 minutes; return potatoes to pan and add the whole eggs. Cook 5 minutes over low heat until potatoes are tender and eggs heated. Serves 8.

title: cathy's hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef; stir in onions and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer until all is tender, about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix and beat well first 4 ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients (next 5 ingredients).
Beginning and ending with dry ingredients, add dry ingredients and zucchini to egg mixture. Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: homemade chocolate cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
If it feels sticky, put in refrigerator.
Bake on silver cookie sheet.
Use ice cream scoop to dip.
Bake at 350°. These cookies are soft cookies.
Bake until golden brown.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer for 10 minutes.
Ready to use.
Good for barbecue chicken.

title: curried shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill well.
Serve on lettuce.
Best if made a day ahead, using fresh, steamed shrimp.
Serves 6.

title: fruited chicken thighs
directions: Trim excess fat from chicken; place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine apple juice, orange juice and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Drain chicken, reserving marinade.
Add raisins, apricots, prunes and ginger to marinade, stirring well.
Arrange onion rings over chicken; pour marinade mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Transfer chicken, onion and fruit to a serving platter, using a slotted spoon; discard cooking liquid to serve. Yield:
6 servings (227 calories per serving).

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until it starts to thicken. Fold in whipped cream.
Cover bottom of 9-inch pan with 1/2 torn angel food cake.
Pour over 1/2 of the strawberries and cream mixture.
Make another layer of rest of torn cake; pour over remaining strawberries and cream mixture.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Cut into squares.
You can use sugar-free jello to further reduce sweetness if that is a dietary need.

title: glazed roasted chicken
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients; reserve half of mixture. Cut chicken in half, and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in a large freezer bag and pour half of teriyaki mixture over chicken.
Chill 8 hours, turning chicken if desired.
Remove chicken from marinade, discarding marinade.
Place chicken, skin side up, on an aluminum foil-lined pan.
Bake at 450 degrees for 45 minutes or on meat thermometer 180.
Brush with rest of teriyaki mixture.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix well with a spoon.
Stir in blueberries.
Pour into paper-lined muffin cups about 2/3 full. An ice cream scoop is perfect to use for muffins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: gracie's rudolph cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350.

title: egg custard (pie)
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, butter, nutmeg, milk and flavoring. Pour into unbaked shell and bake for 20 minutes at 425° and 15 minutes at 325°.
Makes one large pie.

title: beer bread
directions: Pour beer into dry ingredients; stir.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring all ingredients except beets to a boil.
Add cooked beets.
Bring to a boil again and can.
Adding 2 tablespoons lemon juice helps keep beets red.

title: phranic herbal dip
directions: Blend in food processor.
Serve with crackers, chips, bagels, etc.

title: corn dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill overnight. Serve with a large bag of Fritos.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Roll in balls the size of a walnut and roll in white sugar. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Freezes well.

title: ginger cut outs
directions: Stir together the flour, ginger, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine or butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Add the flour mixture; mix well. Cover and chill several hours or until easy to handle.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir.
Microwave for 4 more minutes on High.
Add 1 teaspoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda; stir until light.
Quickly spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break into pieces and store in an airtight container.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast, eggs, sugar, margarine, 2 1/2 cups flour and salt in mixer.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Stir in other 2 cups flour.
Cover and let double in bulk.
Punch gas out. Refrigerate or pinch out and let rise or make crescent rolls. Makes 3 dozen.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: rye popovers
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk and butter.
Add flours and salt.
Beat with wire whisk until smooth.
Pour batter into 6 greased muffin cups, stirring through batter often to prevent settling.
Bake in a 375° oven for 50 minutes.
Prick each popover to let out steam.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve hot.
Makes 6.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients. Trim with fresh fruit slices.
Yields 30 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: In skillet, saute onions and cook ground beef.
In sauce pan, mix and heat beans, rotel (or sauce) and cream of mushroom soup. Add meat after cooked.
In electric skillet, layer tortillas, meat and bean mixture and cheese.
Cook at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Bake pie shells in oven until brown.
Remove and set aside to cool.
In microwave, melt Hershey bars.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Put in refrigerator until set. Can be topped with nuts, if desired.

title: betty's pecan pie
directions: Melt butter, add sugar, syrup and salt; mix well.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice to melted butter; stir until each grain of rice is coated.
In a separate pan, bring chicken broth and water to a boil.
Add parsley and chicken broth to rice. Stir and simmer on low heat with lid on pan.
When all liquid has been absorbed by the rice, remove from heat and let stand at least 2 minutes.

title: mock apple pie
directions: In saucepan, bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to a boil; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Remove from heat and let cool to lukewarm.
Roll out pastry and line pie plate.
Place crackers in crust.
Pour syrup over crackers; do not stir.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add top crust and seal edges.
Slit top crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden.
Cool completely.

title: pepper steak
directions: While rice is cooking, cut steak and sprinkle with paprika. Let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Brown meat in skillet with Pam or some oleo or oil. Add broth. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes. Stir in onion and bell pepper.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more. Blend cornstarch in soy sauce. Stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring, until clear and thickened. Serve over rice with tomato wedges, if you desire.

title: blue ribbon bars
directions: Mix with mixer and spread in sheet cake pan the cake mix, egg and butter.
Press together as if making thick crust.

title: educated potatoes
directions: Combine cooked potatoes, margarine, milk, salt and pepper and mix.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into medium size casserole dish.
Cover with the cheese and bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
You may add bacon bits, cubed ham or diced chicken for variation of flavor.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: best brownies
directions: Beat together.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Bake 35 minutes in 325° oven.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, sugar and 1 1/2 cups cheese together. Pour into greased casserole.
Crush enough Ritz crackers to cover mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over crackers.
Melt butter; drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: beef stew bake
directions: Brown meat in oil. Drain off fat. Combine gravy, tomato juice, water, soup mix and horseradish. Stir into the meat and simmer 5 minutes. Place potatoes in a 2-quart casserole dish. Top with meat mixture and cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours. Stir once or twice.

title: ritzy lemon dessert
directions: Roll crackers fine.
Melt butter and mix with crumbs and powdered sugar.
Take out 1/2 cup crumbs and set aside.
Mix lemonade and Eagle Brand together. Add Cool Whip and pour over crumbs. Sprinkle top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Make sauce by adding the soup, lemon juice and seasonings.
Fold rice and shrimp into sauce. Last fold in sour cream and pour into buttered baking dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top, then decorate with pepper rings. Heat in oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put confectioners sugar, cocoa and milk into glass bowl. Break margarine into cubes.
Mix gently to distribute sugar and cocoa.
Put into microwave on High for 1 minute.
Remove and add vanilla.
Mix thoroughly about 5 minutes until starting to thicken.
Add nuts.
Put on buttered waxed paper and refrigerate about 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, pumpkin, milk, eggs, salt and spice. Sprinkle 1/2 of any cake mix on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan (ungreased).
Gently pour all of pumpkin mixture over cake mix, then sprinkle rest of cake mix over the top.
Melt 1 stick butter and drizzle over top.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: omelet
directions: Heat butter in skillet to medium-low.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper; pour into skillet, covering bottom.
When eggs are almost set (about 1 minute), loosen edge with spatula and fold one-third of omelet toward center; fold other side toward center.
Turn omelet and cook for 1 minute more.
Remove from heat immediately. Inside should be soft and outside should not be crisp.
Serve on warm plate.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt oleo.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking pans.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container.
Pecans or peanuts or both may be added after cooking.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bavarian strawberry cake
directions: Make jello as directed on box.
Put in refrigerator until almost set.
Slice strawberries.
Set aside.
Whip the whipping cream; add some sugar until it forms peaks.
In a very large mixing bowl, tear angel food cake up into bite-size pieces. Slowly mix whipping cream, half of strawberry mixture, yogurt and jello, making sure cake is well coated.
Put in aluminum roasting pan.
Garnish top with remaining strawberries.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Unroll dough.
Press in prepared pan.
Spread taco sauce on crust to within 1 inch of edge.
Sprinkle with half of each cheese.
Top with meat, olives and chilies.
Cover with rest of cheese.
Bake for 17 to 22 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pancakes for "3"
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add egg, milk and shortening.
Mix until all ingredients are wet.
Using a 1/4 measuring cup, pour pancake batter into hot shortening.
Turn only once.

title: finger paints
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in a medium sized saucepan over low heat.
Add cold water and continue stirring until the mixture is thick.
Remove from heat.
Divide the mixture into 4 or 5 portions, spooning them into sections of a muffin tin or small cups.
Add a drop or two of food coloring (a different color for each cup) and a pinch of soap flakes or a drop of detergent to each portion.
Stir and let cool.
You're ready to paint.
Use the shiny side of freezer paper to paint on.
If you have paints left over, they may be stored, covered, in an airtight container.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, brown sugar and sugar for about 1 to 4 minutes.
Add eggs and milk; cream 4 minutes.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Use two teaspoons to roll out cookies.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: sunny veg salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar & vinegar.
Pour over other ingredients in large bowl & toss mixture.
Cover & refrigerate at least an hour.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into a muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until brown on top.
Makes 12.

title: date pudding
directions: Dissolve 1 cup brown sugar in 2 cups boiling water and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, baking powder, dates and nuts.
Drop by spoon into syrup in cake pan. Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes or test with toothpick until it comes out clear.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple in pan. Spread evenly.
Dump cherry pie filling for second layer and spread evenly.
For third layer, add dry yellow cake mix.
Spread evenly; pat gently to make even layer.
Sprinkle chopped nuts evenly over cake mix.
Slice butter pats evenly over cake mix (may need a little more than 1 stick).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: breakfast for overnight guests
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam spray.
Layer croutons, ham, onion, pepper and cheese.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Chill, covered with foil, overnight. Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer.
Serve immediately.
Cut in squares with buttered toast and fresh fruit.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: virginia lee salad
directions: Layer each ingredient into a large bowl, starting with the lettuce.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Completely cover top with salad dressing.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Mix well and serve.

title: steak sauce
directions: Cream all together.
Spread on both sides of steak before broiling.
After broiling, spoon sauce from pan over steaks.

title: easy cheesies
directions: Mix in a large bowl by hand the lemon cake mix, the melted margarine and the egg; press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine lemon frosting mix and cream cheese in a large bowl and mix by hand.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
Spread the rest of it on top of the cake mixture and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then at 300° for 25 minutes, or until light brown.
When completely cool, spread on the reserved cheese frosting and cut into squares.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in skillet.
Add hamburger and brown. Drain excess liquid.
Place frozen spinach on top and cover.
Let simmer until spinach thaws, then mix with hamburger.

title: bread
directions: Put all ingredients together and let it stand until yeast is entirely dissolved.
Put 14 level cups flour (sifted) into a large bowl.
Add the liquid mixture and mix.
Let it raise twice its size.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet mixed table relish
directions: Put vegetables through chopper or chop fine by hand.
Place in kettle with other ingredients.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Pack and seal in sterile jars, about 6 pints.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together until done.
Add next 5 ingredients to potatoes.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 13 by 9 by 2 inch pan. Cool. Take half of cake and break into small pieces. Put in punch bowl. Prepare pudding and let stand until thickened. Then put half of pudding over cake, then half of pineapple, including juice; 1 can cherry pie filling; one carton Cool Whip; and half of nuts. Repeat with rest of ingredients. Add a few maraschino cherries on top to decorate.

title: copper coins (carrots)
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salted water (with a little garlic if desired).
When cool, drain and alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion rings (sliced thin).
In 1 1/2-quart casserole or bowl of equal size, make marinade of remaining ingredients, blending well.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight. Good for 1 week.
Drain to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Line pie plate with plain pastry.
Cut bacon in small pieces and saute until crisp.
Sprinkle half of crisp bacon on pastry. Mix other ingredients and pour into shell.
Sprinkle remaining crisp bacon pieces on top.
Bake 5 minutes at 450°.
Lower heat to 325° and bake until custard is firm.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix cherries, Karo, sugar, vanilla, almond extract and cornstarch together.
Top with cake mix.
Melt oleo on top and sprinkle on pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour and milk.
Mix well.
Add coconut to mixture.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Spoon cherries over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, brown sugar, melted butter and cinnamon until crumbly.
Press half of the mixture into a greased 9-inch baking pan.
Cover crunch mixture with diced rhubarb.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water, and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour this sauce over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm, plain or topped with whipped cream.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: Chop onions, celery and green peppers.
Mince garlic.
Cut sausage lengthwise into quarters and then into thin slices.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions, celery and garlic and cook until soft, about 10 minutes.
Add green peppers and sausage.
Cook until very soft, about 10 minutes.
Drain tomatoes.
Reserve liquid.
Add tomatoes and break up with a spoon.
Add herbs, cayenne, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 2 teaspoons black pepper.
Add enough stock to reserved tomato liquid to make 5 cups.
Add with rice to pan.
Cover and simmer on low until rice is almost done, 15 to 18 minutes.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Add shrimp and cook until they just turn pink, 3 to 8 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Place gelatin and pineapple in saucepan; bring to a boil. Cool.
Mix pimento, salt and cheese until blended.
Mix with gelatin mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts; pour into mold. Chill until set.

title: apple pie
directions: Dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: two-tone fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly, over moderate heat.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
To 2 cups mixture, add butterscotch pieces and 1/2 cup walnuts; blend well.
Pour evenly into greased 9-inch square pan.
To remaining hot mixture, add chocolate pieces and 1/2 cup walnuts; blend well.
Pour over butterscotch mixture.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer all of these ingredients and toss with the Catalina dressing.

title: yum-yum four layer dessert
directions: Combine and pat in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 15 minutes).
Let cool.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Heat soup and milk.
Do not boil.
Melt the cheese in the sauce.
In butter, simmer onion and green pepper.
Add pimento to sauce.
Season to taste.
Cook noodles.

title: honey chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together honey and butter.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture. Blend well.
Add vanilla and chocolate chips.
Mix well.

title: stained glass window cookie
directions: Melt chocolate bits with butter.
Break in eggs, add sugar, cookie wafers, nuts and marshmallows.
Mix.
Lay a piece of plastic wrap on counter.
Shape dough on it into a roll about 1 1/2 inch thick.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill.
Slice and eat.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In bowl, blend together sour cream, Cool Whip, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into 4 1/2-cup ring mold.
Freeze overnight.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with additional cherries.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: swiss steak
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Remove vegetables.
Add meat and brown on both sides.
Return vegetables and cover with canned tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours or meat is tender.

title: mom's jello cheesecake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and set aside.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Combine first and second mixtures and set aside to cool.
Combine crackers and butter. Pack into bottom of an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Save a couple of handfuls for the top.
Whip milk (well chilled).
Blend with Jell-O mixture and pour over crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top. Chill several hours.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, salt, syrup and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Boil to 265° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; pour half of the syrup slowly over egg whites, beating with electric mixer.
Return syrup to stove. Cook to 300°.
Pour slowly over egg white mixture.
Beat until stiff. Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat by hand until firm. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Let stand until firm.
Store in airtight container.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large roasting pan, toss all ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes, stirring once, until potatoes are tender.
Great with lamb or beef roasts.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Mix crab, onions, cucumber and egg.
Then mix remaining ingredients and stir into crab mixture.
Chill.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Put baking soda in applesauce and stir.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Sift flour and spices.
Stir all together with remaining ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Do not crowd. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 355°.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: marinade for london broil roast
directions: Stick holes in meat and pour marinade over it.
Marinate overnight or at least 6 hours, turning occasionally.

title: holiday brunch casserole
directions: Layer sausage, mushrooms, green onions, tomatoes and cheese in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Beat remaining ingredients; pour over sausage mixture. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until golden brown. Cool about 30 minutes. Cut into 12 (3-inch) squares. Serves 12.

title: oven crisp chicken
directions: Mix ingredients except butter.
Dip desired chicken pieces in butter and cover with crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350° after drizzling butter over chicken; cover pan with foil.

title: instant eggnog(no-fat, no cholesterol)
directions: Fresh eggs no longer are safely used raw because of salmonella bacteria.

title: 30 minute corned beef and cabbage dinner
directions: In a large saucepan, combine broth, garlic, caraway seed and pepper; heat to a boil.
Add cabbage and carrots.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer 15 to 17 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Place corned beef over vegetables in pan.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until corned beef is heated through.
Arrange corned beef and vegetables on large serving platter; spoon remaining cooking liquid over top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: judy's spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Make into balls. Freeze. When ready to use, bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Mini-muffin pans are perfect size for baking. Or, you can microwave them on high for 5 minutes.

title: easy cheese danish
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay flat in pan one package of crescent rolls.
Cream the cream cheese, 1 egg yolk, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Lay second package of crescent rolls on top and coat with egg white.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix real good; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and press down.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for 1 hour before serving or can be eaten immediately.
Serves 6 or more.

title: homestyle rice
directions: In a meat loaf pan, combine all ingredients and mix well. Seal pan snugly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° until rice is tender.
Takes about 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Melt yeast in half water heated to tepid.
Mix all ingredients, except flour.
Gradually mix in flour until mixture sticks together to form ball.
Turn out on floured board; knead only 3 to 4 times.
Place in lightly greased bowl.
Cover with white cloth; let rise 2 hours.
Punch down.
Place cover on dish. Refrigerate and pinch off as needed.
Put in desired shape. Let rise again.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: mama's coconut pie
directions: Mix
sugar, flour and salt together.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk to the sugar mixture.	Add coconut.
Bake in unbaked crusts for 25
to	30 minutes at 350° for 3 thin pies.
If you bake 2 thick pies, cook longer.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, cheese, sour cream and pepper.
Pour in 1 quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Mix glaze and berries together; put on cake.
Mix pudding as directed and put on top of berries.
Put Cool Whip on top of pudding.

title: carrot squares
directions: Beat
together	the
sugar,
salad
oil
and eggs.
Add carrots.
Sift the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 large pan or 2 smaller ones.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Drain 2 small cans of lima beans or 1 large can Great Northern beans.
Add 1 regular can baked beans. Mix all together with 4 slices fried bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
This can be used on spare ribs, leftover meats or add hot sauce and brush on chicken wings before grilling.

title: strawberry, walnut and banana parfait
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together sour cream, milk, sugar and allspice.
Add sliced strawberries and bananas.
Mix well.
In 4 to 5 dessert bowls, spoon in even amounts of mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: pineapple fluff(low-fat for diabetics)
directions: Mix graham crackers, 4 packs Equal and margarine together. Press into a 7 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Blend cream cheese, 6 packs sweetener, vanilla and Cool Whip. Stir in pineapple. Pour on top of cooled graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: apple potato cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 tablespoon oleo and brush on cut surfaces of squash.
Place cut side down in a large baking dish without crowding.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
In medium skillet, melt remaining oleo and saute remaining ingredients 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spoon vegetables into squash halves.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix until fluffy.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook and stir crumbled beef and onion in skillet until beef is brown.
Drain and stir in salt and pepper. Spread beef mixture in lightly greased 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese. Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour over mixture in pie plate.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oil cake
directions: Add ingredients as listed.
Mix dry ingredients; add milk and vanilla.
Mix.
Add eggs and mix.
Add oil and water and beat well.
Place in sprayed pan.
Makes 1 large sheet cake or 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Early in day or day ahead:
In large saucepot or Dutch oven, place ribs and cover with water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until ribs are fork-tender.
Remove to platter and refrigerate.

title: spicy rolls
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Add spices to butter and mix well. Coat the biscuit pieces with this mixture.
Place pieces into muffin pans (4 pieces to a section).
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: swiss meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg and add all ingredients, reserving 1/4 cup cheese.
Form into a loaf in a 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake a few minutes more to melt cheese.

title: wendy's german chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake as package directs.
Bake 1/2 of cake mix in greased and floured cake pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
On top of stove, melt butter, caramel candies and milk.
Remove from heat.
Cool mixture SLIGHTLY.
Pour over baked half of cake.
Pour remaining cake batter on top of caramel.
Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and slick dumplings
directions: Combine chicken, water and salt in large Dutch oven; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours (until tender). If necessary, add water to maintain at least 3 cups broth.
Remove chicken from broth; cool.
Bone and cut into bite-size pieces. Return to broth and set aside.

title: pound cake
directions: Follow in order of recipe.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Do not preheat oven!

title: smackin cake
directions: Mix ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
You can sprinkle with nuts, coconut or chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: johnnycake
directions: Preheat the
oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch baking pan. Sift flour,
corn meal, baking powder and salt together.
Beat the egg and add the sugar.	Warm the milk slightly with honey, stirring thoroughly.
Add
the
sugar,
milk and cooking oil. Mix thoroughly.
Combine with the dry ingredients gradually to avoid lumps.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serve while hot.

title: cholesterol free fruit pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and, if desired, you can add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg to the apple pie. Using cholesterol free pie crust, fill with apple or peach mixture.
Dot with corn oil margarine and cover with top crust. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Cut slits in top crust and set pan on pizza pan or something larger than your pie pan so it won't run over in oven.

title: caesar salad
directions: Put peeled and sliced garlic in olive oil for 24 hours.
Saute French bread in 2 tablespoons of garlic oil.
Break up romaine into 1-inch lengths and place in salad bowl.
Sprinkle salt, dry mustard, black pepper, anchovy and Worcestershire sauce over romaine.
Add wine vinegar and the remaining 6 tablespoons garlic oil.
Cook gently in simmering water for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or use one raw egg.
Drop the egg from the shell onto the ingredients in the bowl.
Squeeze the juice of 1 lemon over egg.
Add the croutons and 2 to 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Toss the salad well.
Serve at once.

title: baked ziti
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package; cook only 7 minutes. Drain; set aside.
Brown beef, garlic and onions; drain.
Mix cooked beef mixture, pasta, seasonings and spaghetti sauce in large bowl.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's candy balls
directions: Combine sugar, milk, pecans and coconut in very large mixing bowl.
Pour melted oleo over all ingredients.
Using your hands, mix well until you can form it into a firm ball.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll into small balls and refrigerate again until hard.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in Dutch pan. Using a toothpick, dip balls into mixture and set on wax paper. Fill toothpick holes, using a small spoon.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Slice pickles into original jar, alternating layers of slices pickles and sugar.
Add garlic pickling spices.
Cover with pickle juice.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: seafood supreme
directions: Make 2 cups of white sauce, very thick.
Season with onion salt, Old Bay seasoning and Tabasco (you may need more seasonings later).
Cut up sealegs and put in sauce.
Grate a fair chunk of cheese (can use any kind if you do not have Monterey Jack). Reheat until bubbly.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Bring two cups of water to a boil and place cauliflower, broken into flowerets, and onion in water and cook until tender. Place (including water) into blender and blend until smooth.
Set aside.
Mix butter and flour and mix in 1 cup water gradually. Heat until it starts to boil.
Stir in blender mix and rest of ingredients, except cream.
Heat until it just boils and add cream.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well. Mash bananas in another bowl.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Put bananas in butter-sugar mixture.
Gradually add flour mixture, blending well.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° about 40 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken until meat almost falls off bone.
Remove from bone in large pieces.
Brown onion and bell pepper in butter. Combine chicken, onion, bell pepper, tomatoes, paprika, catsup, salt and pepper.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti and mushroom soup or sliced mushrooms with the coffee cream.
Mix well.
Add grated cheese on top of casserole and heat in oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 12.

title: italian chicken
directions: Heat oil.
Dip chicken breasts in egg mixture and roll in Italian bread crumbs.
Fry on medium-high until completely cooked and golden brown.
Drain on a paper towel.
Arrange chicken on a baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over chicken and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until sauce and cheese is bubbling. Serve with fettucini, Italian salad and garlic bread.

title: edible clay
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add more powdered sugar if needed to improve consistency.
Children can play with it and eat it.

title: fruit juice tapioca dessert
directions: *One and one-half cups with orange juice, one-third cup with apple juice; 1/4 cup and 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg with cider or, if leftover juices, taste and add sugar to your taste.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Arrange beef cubes in a baking dish large enough to hold single layer.
Cut up vegetables in good size chunks.
Layer on top of meat.
Mix together tomato sauce, water and sugar; pour over ingredients.
Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle flour over the top.
Don't bother to stir in.
Seal tightly in foil.
Place in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
Don't peek during cooking time.
The meat will be browned with perfect gravy.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Put meat into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer potatoes, onions and mushrooms over meat.
Pour soups over all.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, vanilla, dates, sugar, milk, salt and walnuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine in a saucepan the brown sugar, butter and water.
Bring mixture to a boil, then pour over batter mixture.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: fried chicken delight
directions: *Sandwich cuts are best and smoked gives an Ozark flavor.

title: killed lettuce
directions: In large bowl, tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Mix with onions.
Heat together in small frying pan the grease, milk, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Do not let boil.
Cool slightly.
Pour over lettuce.
Amount of sugar depends on taste; I use about 1 tablespoon.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Pound chicken breast until thin.
Combine flour or bread crumbs with salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Saute in pan with butter until cooked.
Remove from pan.
Take juice from 1 lemon and a little water and pour into the pan to make gravy. Return chicken to pan with gravy and serve.

title: company chicken
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, shred corned beef.
Wrap a piece of bacon around each chicken breast half and place on top of the beef.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour on top of the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve with rice and/or biscuits.
Serves 8.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water; drain.
Steam cabbage. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Drain.
Saute onions and butter or margarine until lightly browned.
Mix noodles, cabbage, butter and onions together.

title: zesty broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions then drain. Combine soups, cheese, egg and milk (mixed together) and mayonnaise.
Stir into drained broccoli.
Spoon into a greased 2-pint casserole dish.
Combine butter and crumbs; sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: favorite pumpkin squares
directions: Combine
pumpkin,
sugar and spices.
Add pecans.
In a chilled
bowl,
fold
pumpkin
mixture
into
ice cream.
Line bottom of 13
x 9 x 2-inch pan with half the gingersnaps.
Top with half
the ice cream mixture.
Repeat.	Freeze until firm, about 5 hours.
Cut in squares, garnish with whipped cream and pecan halves, if desired.
Makes 18 servings.

title: hershey's bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars and marshmallows with milk over low fire; cool.
Whip cream; add to mixture and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix and bake in tube pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix oleo with sugar; add egg, beating until creamy.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Fold in blueberries (fresh or thawed frozen), being careful not to crush the berries.
Spread batter in muffin pans or paper baking cups, 2/3 full.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on each muffin. Dot with oleo and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Also good as coffeecake.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sis' sugar cookies
directions: In medium bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, cream margarine, salad oil, confectioners sugar and 1 cup granulated sugar until lightly fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; continue beating, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Gradually add dry ingredients and continue mixing until just combined.
Wrap and refrigerate dough at least 1 hour.

title: bubble pizza
directions: In a greased 9x12-inch pan lay the biscuts on the bottom of the pan.
Spread sauce.
Add hamburger, onions, green peppers, mushrooms and olives.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Cook (boil) chicken breasts until done; save 1 cup broth. Pull chicken off bones; cut in bite size pieces.
Set aside. After baking corn bread, let cool.
Crumble up corn bread fine; pour melted margarine over corn bread.
Mix well and set aside.

title: plain sugared nuts
directions: Boil sugar and water until spins thread on fork.
Remove from fire and add vanilla or almond flavoring.
Stir in nuts until cloudy.
Pour on cookie sheet; separate with fork.

title: slow and easy chuck roast
directions: Cut away as much fat as possible from roast.
Sprinkle roast with next 3 ingredients and place in crock-pot, add water and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serves 6.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crumble graham crackers; add raisins, pecans, coconut and cherries.
Melt butter and marshmallows in top of double boiler; add cherry juice.
Combine the two mixtures, mixing well.
Pack in container and refrigerate.

title: brie with apples
directions: Open Brie and place on microwave-safe dish.
Put other ingredients except apples on top of cheese.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve with apple pieces surrounding cheese mix for dipping.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage in a skillet until it loses its pink color, stirring to break up sausage; drain off fat.
Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese thoroughly and form into 1-inch balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet until brown in 350°
oven.
Yields approximately 5 dozen.

title: baked un-fried chicken tenders
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
In a smaller bowl, place the yogurt.
Rinse chicken in very cold water. Coat each chicken tender with yogurt, then coat with crumb mixture.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift
together
in mixing bowl flour, salt
and
baking powder.
Add eggs and stir in milk.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in cooked corn.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot fat at 370° and fry until golden.
Salt lightly.

title: spanish steak
directions: Pound steak, cut into serving size pieces and dredge in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Brown steak on both sides in oil. Add onions and green pepper and saute.
Then add tomatoes; cover and cook until steak is tender, about an hour.
Cook slowly in a large skillet.
Excellent covered with mashed potatoes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: low-fat lemon dessert
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on box.
Add the lemon jello (dry) into the hot pudding.
Let cool.
Fold in carton of lite Cool Whip.
Fold in cut up angel food cake.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
Cut and serve.

title: mama's yummy pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; set aside.
Add extract to milk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch chops in double boiler. Add Rice Krispies and marshmallows; mix well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: egg squares
directions: Lay rolls in bottom of pan.
Put cheese over rolls.
Spread evenly. Add cooked sausage.
Whip eggs, soup, salt, pepper and green peppers.
Pour over sausage evenly. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Turn into a large bowl.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Using electric mixer, beat at medium speed until batter is smooth.
Stir in nuts, carrots and pineapple. Turn batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake about 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: spanish paella
directions: Grill or quick-fry meat, then cut into bite-sized pieces.
Add meat to sauce and slightly blend.
Do not overstir or cook.
Serve vegetable and meat sauce over rice.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Gradually add sugar.
Add oil and combined dry ingredients alternately with grated zucchini.
Stir in chopped walnuts, raisins and vanilla.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans on lower rack at 350° for approximately 55 minutes.
Turn onto cooling racks.
Freezes well.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fruit pectin, in Dutch oven; bring mixture to a boil, stirring occasionally, until the sugar dissolves.

title: strawberry-banana pie
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in water. Blend in cream cheese until smooth. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into pie crust. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; refrigerate for 24 hours.
Drain off liquid.
Mix the sugar and white vinegar; add first mixture.
Mix and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Put in covered containers and freeze.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Cream eggs, beat well.
Add flour and milk a little at a time.
Add bananas and vanilla last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
*1 tablespoon vinegar to almost 1/2 cup milk.

title: cheese and vegetable canapes
directions: Stir together cream cheese and chives or green onions; set aside. Slice each squash on the diagonal into 1 inch slices. Spoon the cheese mixture into a decorative or a heavy, large food-storage bag and snip one corner. Pipe the cheese mixture onto the squash slices. Sprinkle each slice with either the radish or carrot. Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: herbed zucchini fans
directions: To make zucchini fans, slice each squash lengthwise, making cuts 1/4 inch apart, leaving slices attached at stem end.
Fan out slices and brush both sides with vegetable oil.
Grill squash fans over medium-hot coals three to five minutes on each side or until tender.
Meanwhile, combine margarine, mustard, thyme and pepper. Drizzle over cooked zucchini fans.
Yields 4 servings.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs on all sides.
Saute onion in
hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly until flavors are well blended, 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in oven at 350°.

title: strawberry fruit ice
directions: Mix the juices, sugar, fruits and yogurt; put in freezer until almost set.
Beat with mixer on high speed until creamy and fluffy.
Cover and return to freezer.
If fruit ice is made ahead of time, must be rebeaten, then put in the freezer for a little while.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ham and corn skillet
directions: Brown ham in butter.
Add corn, seasonings and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until eggs are set.
Serves 6.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onion; separate rings.
Mix milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Dip each onion ring in batter; fry in heated oil (375°) until golden, turning once.

title: korean-style beef
directions: Combine wine, soy sauce, honey, green onions, sesame oil, ginger root and garlic in a large baking dish.
Add flank steak. Marinate, covered, in refrigerator about one hour, turning at least once.

title: quick apple pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large pie plate.
Mix remainder of ingredients and spread over top of apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: 24 hour waldorf salad
directions: In a bowl, toss apples with lemon juice.
Stir in celery, nuts, raisins and grapes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs; beat well! Add the tartar and soda; beat well. Work in the flour. Form dough into rolls; wrap in waxed paper. Refrigerate in covered pan (up to 2 weeks). Slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° approximately 7 to 10 minutes. Serve with LOVE.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven-fried catfish
directions: Wash fish and drain slightly.
Mix cornmeal and spices together.
Place in a bag.
Bread fish with mix.
Brush a dark baking sheet with the oil and place fish on the pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn over and continue baking until done.

title: filling for dark fruit cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Cook in a double boiler until quite thick.

title: veggie salad
directions: Cube vegetables and place into a bowl.
Pour buttermilk over vegetables and mix well.
Pour cornmeal over this and mix well. Fry in a skillet with butter and oil until brown.

title: summertime quencher
directions: Cut lemon and orange in half crosswise. Cut 1 lemon half and 1 orange half into 1/4-inch-thick slices.

Squeeze juice from remaining halves. Place juice in a 2-quart pitcher. Stir in wine, carbonated beverage, lemon and orange slices and remaining fruit. Serve over ice. Makes about 8 (5-ounce) servings.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pork chops in shallow Pyrex baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place 1 tablespoon of butter on each and spread, then 1 tablespoon of brown sugar on each.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday oyster casserole
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, butter, salt and pepper together.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with 1/3 of the cracker crumbs. Add 1/2 of the oysters. Add another 1/3 of the cracker crumbs. Add the rest of the oysters.
Pour milk and Worcestershire sauce mixture over the above. Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs over the top. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Bring crushed pineapple to a boil and remove from heat.
Add orange Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Stir in buttermilk.
When mixture is cool, add coconut, pecans and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly, using mixer.
Grease 2 loaf pans. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: pillsbury chocolate chip squares
directions: Cut roll in half.
Place half back in refrigerator.
Take other half, slice and place slices in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan to soften.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients and mix well with electric mixer.
Press cookie dough evenly on bottom (keeping hands wet helps dough not to stick too much to hands). Pour cream cheese mixture into pan.
Take other half of cookie roll and break into small pieces all over cream cheese mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool and slice into squares.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes (35 minutes for glass baking dish).

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil raisins, dates and apple in the 1 cup water for 3 minutes.
Add shortening.
Cool.
Add the other ingredients. Chill.
Drop from teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Store in refrigerator.

title: baked pretzel pieces
directions: Melt butter.
Place pretzels in paper bag, adding melted butter and soup mix.
Shake well.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 1 1/2 hours at 250°, stirring half way through.
Cool and put in airtight container.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Stir lemon juice into milk.
Add egg yolks and stir.
Pour in pie shell.
Beat egg whites and and sugar.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding enough flour to make stiff dough.
Bake at 350°.

title: chop suey
directions: Simmer pork with celery and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste; add mushrooms with liquid.
Shortly before serving, add drained bean sprouts.
Serve over hot rice and add soy sauce.

title: garlicky clam dip
directions: Using garlic press, squeeze garlic pulp and juice into softened cheese.
Cream with a spoon until smooth.
Gradually add the remaining ingredients, blending until smooth.
For thinner dip, add more clam broth.
Serve with crackers, chips or veggies. Yield:
8 servings.

title: fried eggs
directions: In fry pan over medium heat, cook butter until just hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
(If a very large pan is used, more butter will be needed.)
Break and slip eggs gently into pan. Reduce heat immediately.
Cook slowly to desire doneness, spooning butter over eggs to baste or turning eggs to cook both sides.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix well and serve as is or can stuff tomatoes, using insides in ingredients.

title: salmon spread
directions: In medium-size bowl, blend salmon, cream cheese, onions, lemon juice, horseradish, pickle relish and salt.
Wrap in wax paper and form into ball.
Chill until firm, about 1 hour.

title: quick 100% whole wheat bread
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a small bowl and let stand for about 10 minutes.
In a large separate bowl, mix the hot water, honey, oil, salt and 4 cups whole wheat flour in order given.
Cool to lukewarm and add yeast mixture.
Beat thoroughly in electric mixer or vigorously by hand.
Let this rise in a warm place 15 minutes.
Add enough of the 5 cups of warmed flour to make soft dough which can be handled.
Knead 5 minutes.
Throw the mass of dough with force onto the bread board several times.
Put loaves into well-greased pans and allow to sit for 12 minutes.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Increase heat to 350° and finish baking, about 45 minutes.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 well-greased, hot iron skillets.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 4 to 5 minutes.

title: blueberry kuchen
directions: Crush zwieback crackers.
Pour crumbs in a 9 x 9-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top, then pour the blueberries on.
Top with brown sugar and place in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip and set overnight. Also mix jello to set.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler. Add tomatoes and mix well. Serve warm as a dip with tortilla chips, corn chips or crackers.
Also may be used as a sauce over meats and vegetables.

title: jack daniels' marinade
directions: Marinate steaks 2 to 6 hours before grilling.
Good for Pork Medallions also.

title: mix fruit jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and put strawberries, bananas and pineapple in.
Pour half into mold and let firm.
Remove after jelled; mix sour cream and nuts and spread on top.
Pour remaining mixture on top and jell until firm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook 7 or 8 minutes until it begins to thicken.
When cool and beginning to set, pour over 1 quart of washed and hulled strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.
Serve with whipped topping.
Makes two 8-inch pies or 1 large.

title: leek soup
directions: Saute the leeks and mushrooms in olive oil.
When soft, add to broth.
Boil for 10 minutes and add white wine.
Add pasta and simmer until cooked, approximately 7 to 10 minutes.
Serve and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar.
Add zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture.
Add sour cream and nuts and raisins, if desired.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir together.
Put on medium heat and stir until the sugars are dissolved and the mixture begins to boil.
Turn down heat and boil gently for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat and stir in maple flavoring.
Put in a maple syrup container or jar.
Makes 2 cups.

title: mom's bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Use large container.
Put garlic, cucumbers, ice and salt in container.
Leave 3 hours.
Boil vinegar and sugar with spices.
Drop cucumbers and onions into hot vinegar solution until they turn color.
Spoon into quart jars.
Turn jars upside down until cool.

title: s'mores
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients over
low heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large bowl.
Mix quickly and add marshmallows.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan; press mixture evenly.

title: moors and christians(from cuba)
directions: Amounts and sizes of the ingredients herein depend entirely on the size duck one starts out with.
A young, fat duck is rubbed inside and out with salt and pepper.
Stuff with enough bread crumbs to fill the cavity, which has been moistened with a semi-dry white cooking wine or saki or Chinese rice wine.
Add 4 tablespoons of blanched almonds, pureed to paste with 1 tablespoon ice water and 2 pinches of anise seed plus 1/4 teaspoon powdered ginger.
Blend well. Stuff bird and sew up cavity.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend on "blend" for one minute.
Pour in a 9-inch greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean. Cool and chill.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish. Cover with noodles.
Cover and bake 40 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with the jacket on.
Fry bacon crisp; remove from pan.
Add water and vinegar; let simmer for a few minutes. Mix flour and sugar and add to water and vinegar mixture.
Let simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Peel and slice potatoes; add onion, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over potatoes while it is hot and serve potatoes warm.

title: cheese cake
directions: Take out 1 cup dry cake mix and reserve.
To remaining cake mix add oil and egg.
Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.

title: low calorie shake
directions: Crush ice cubes in a blender.
Add milk, fruit and sweetener. Blend into a frothy delicious shake.

title: herb bread with beer
directions: *Or 1 1/2 tablespoons of chives instead of rosemary.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Crush Oreos.
Fold into softened ice cream, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Turn into a 13 x 9-inch pan and cover.
Freeze.
Cut into squares before serving.
Keeps well.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and put into soup pot. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer gently for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Spread broken pretzels in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish; mix oleo and sugar and pour over pretzels.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over pretzels.
Dissolve jello in water and add strawberries. Pour over top, covering Cool Whip-cream cheese mixture.
Chill to set.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in casserole dish with consomme and onion soup.
Add rice and stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: diane's rice dish
directions: Melt Butter in casserole dish in oven.
Add all ingredients to casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli
directions: Mix together.
Top with 1/2 cup Ritz cracker crumbs.
Dab with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered.

title: venison stew
directions: Salt and pepper venison cubes.
Brown lightly in skillet in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Put celery and onion in slow pot.
Add browned cubes and all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on medium 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: cheese-garlic bread
directions: Combine butter, garlic and oregano.
Spread on Italian bread. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, then broil for last few minutes.

title: baked beefy beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper, salt and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients in medium bowl and then add to ground beef with 1/2 cup water.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: roasted rosemary chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, cook garlic cloves and rosemary in hot olive oil over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until garlic is soft (watch garlic closely to avoid burning).
Remove garlic with a slotted spoon and set aside, reserving the oil mixture.
Let oil mixture cool.
Stir lemon juice, pepper and salt into oil.
Wash the chicken thoroughly; pat dry with paper towels.
Season body cavity with salt.
Pull the neck skin to the back and fasten with a small skewer.
If a band of skin crosses the tail, tuck the drumsticks under the band.
If there is no band, tie the drumsticks securely to the tail.
Twist wing tips under the back.
Place the chicken, breast side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Cut five slits randomly in the chicken skin, large enough to insert a garlic clove under the skin.
Insert 5 garlic cloves.
Reserve remaining garlic for Garlic Mashed Potatoes.
Brush chicken with some of the olive oil mixture.
Insert meat thermometer into the center of one of the inside thigh muscles.
The bulb should not touch the bone.

title: nutty baked chicken
directions: Lightly toss the chicken, celery and pecans together.
Puree a sauce of the mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and 1 cup cheese in a blender.
Toss the chicken mixture with the sauce.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer on plate the beans, sour cream mixed with seasoning, guacamole, lettuce, tomato, olives, cheeses and onion and peppers if desired.
Refrigerate 2 hours; serve with taco chips.

title: easy chicken enchilada
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole starting with tortillas, chicken (pieces), green chilies and cheese.
Makes approximately 4 layers.
Top with cheese after covering with green sauce.
Cook in 350° oven approximately 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Season chicken and place in baking dish. Bake chicken for 30 minutes. Melt butter. Add teriyaki, pineapple chunks, and brown sugar to butter and pour over chicken. Bake for another 30 minutes on 350.

title: tandoori chicken salad
directions: Combine yogurt, lemon juice, garlic, bouillon, water, cumin, ginger, mustard and red pepper; mix well. In shallow dish, pour 1/2 cup bouillon mixture over chicken. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 6 hours or overnight. Chill remaining mixture to use for salad dressing. Remove chicken from marinade. Heat marinade. Grill or broil chicken, basting with marinade.

title: italian rice balls
directions: Cook rice in salted water, rinse in cold water and drain.
Add eggs.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Then form into balls and dip in egg and bread crumbs.
Fry in oil.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel potatoes and cut them into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Place slices in a bowl with oil, salt, pepper and thyme or other herbs.
Toss to mix well.
Place the slices on a baking sheet sprayed with Pam, spreading the slices so they overlay slightly.
Bake, uncovered, for about 20 minutes or longer if you prefer them crisper.
Serves 4.
Contains 195 calories per serving.

title: sweet -n- tart
directions: Whirl all ingredients in a blender until smooth and thick.

title: barbecued baby back ribs
directions: Put ribs in large pan.
Cover with water and pour in liquid smoke.
Boil until so tender when you put in a fork, it slides right back out.
Drain.
Just before you are ready to serve, brush both sides with barbecue sauce real good.
Place on broiler and heat both sides until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: tropical fruit cocktail
directions: In small bowl, combine juices, sugar, ginger root and jalapeno; stir to mix and partially dissolve sugar.
Set aside. In large bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Stir juice mixture again to blend.
Drizzle over fruit and stir to coat.
If time permits, marinate at least 1 hour in refrigerator before serving. Garnish with mint leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: polynesian ham
directions: Place sliced ham on cookie sheet.
Place sliced pineapple on top of ham.
Pour juice over ham.
Place in oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Take out; let cool for about 10 minutes.
Roll ham up; put pineapple and cherry on with toothpick.
Place back in oven for 10 minutes.
Using about 12 to 15 pieces of ham will serve 6 to 7 people.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar, flour and salt with a small amount of water.
Heat the mixture.
Line pie plate with pastry and fill with rhubarb mixture; dot with butter and cover with top crust. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: gracious garnish
directions: Place prunes in deep dish, cover with red wine and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Use a side garnish with meats, fish or simply enjoy it as is.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer in order of ingredients.
Keep in layers; do not mix together.
Mix in separate bowl Miracle Whip and sugar.
Spread on top of salad.
Cover with lid or foil and let sit in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.
Mix just before serving.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix crumbs, Parmesan, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in mixture until well coated.
Place in a 10 x 10-inch baking pan, skin side up.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes, then turn chicken and bake 20 minutes more.

title: banana salad
directions: Cut bananas into chunks, mix in lemon juice to coat each chunk.
