Mix together sugar, sour cream, Cool Whip, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add bananas.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: greek salad
directions: Place lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon in order in serving bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese and sugar until well blended and spread ingredients in bowl; seal completely to the edge.
Let stand several hours in refrigerator before mixing and serving (can be made the day before).
Also, the remaining salad will stay crisp for several days if kept in a tight container.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use enough milk to make mixture fall off spoon.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed and cool.
Crumble 1/2 of the cake in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Using the milk, prepare pudding.
Pour half over crumbled cake.
Spread 1 can cherry filling, then 1 can drained pineapple.
Spreads on 1/2 of the Cool Whip, then half of the nuts.
Repeat steps with same ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put mixture into baking pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: ron's favorite oatmeal pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs together, then add syrup, oats, coconut and vanilla.
Put into large unbaked shell.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Preheat oven to 425° and bake for 15 minutes.
Turn down oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: ann's easy pudding and sauce cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and pour into 2-inch deep baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Mix together the sugar, salt and cocoa. Sprinkle this over batter.
Pour the water over. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: holiday dream bars
directions: Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups brown sugar.
Add flour, mixing well.
Press mixture into 12 x 17 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs until thick.
Add 3 1/2 cups brown sugar and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except powdered sugar and mix thoroughly.
Pour over baked crust and bake an additional 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into bars.

title: hard-times cake
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into layer pan; bake until done. Spread with jelly or fruit.

title: country cheese ball
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients. Mix well. Shape into ball. Coat with remaining ham and chill.

title: mama's lemon or orange pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs slowly.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately.
Add flavoring, juice and coloring.
Fold in rind.

title: microwave strawberry-banana cobbler
directions: Peel and slice bananas; place in 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix pie filling, lemon juice and vanilla.
Spoon over bananas. Micro-cook uncovered 6 minutes, turning dish every 2 minutes.
Mix cookies and pecans; sprinkle over fruit.
Cook uncovered 1 minute. Serve warm with ice cream or light cream.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat sugar and spices into beaten eggs.
Stir in orange and lemon juices.
Cut ice cream in chunks.
Place in punch bowl. Slowly pour ginger ale.
Stir in egg mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 20 servings.

title: banana blueberry mini-loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease and flour bottoms only of three 6 x 3-1/2 inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, combine Sugar and Oil and beat well.
Add mashed Bananas, Yogurt, Vanilla and Eggs mixing well.
Add Flour, Baking Soda and salt; stir just until ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir in Blueberries.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 30 - 40 minutes.
Cool five minutes - remove from pans.
Cool completely.

title: mad russian atomic balm(modified from a sunset magazine recipe, july 1993)
directions: Place all ingredients gently into a 3-quart saucepan.
Stir often over medium heat until just at boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for about 20 minutes to blend the flavors.
Let cool.
Cover.
Chill.

title: chocolate puff souffle
directions: In top of double boiler, over hot water, put first 3 ingredients.
When melted together, stir and add vanilla and eggs. Beat well with eggbeater for three minutes.
Cover and cook for thirty minutes (or longer if more convenient) without lifting cover, until serving.
Serve with cream (whipped and seasoned) or plain light cream, as is.

title: mamaw bea's blue ribbon banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased baking pan (loaf).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: venison pie
directions: Roll out half of pie dough and place in a 9-inch pie plate. Mix venison and remaining ingredients.
Place half of mixture on pie dough in pie pan.
Fold dough over filling to make half-moon shape that fills one-half of the pie plate.
Seal and crimp edges of dough.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly 3/4 cup sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Measure 2 cups flour by the dip-level-pour method.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in.
Blend in berries. Spread in greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
For crumb topping, mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour, cinnamon and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick stuck into center comes out clean.
Serve warm. Makes nine 3-inch squares.

title: hearty tomato sauce
directions: Start with large pot.
Add both cans V-8 juice, vinegar, basil and sugar.
Get large skillet with olive oil.
Heat until hot. Add onions, garlic, green peppers and hamburger.
Cook sausages in small skillet.
When done, drain sausages.
Dice up and add to large skillet.
When all is done, add to large pot.
Simmer for 75 minutes.

title: alaskan king crab au gratin
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add milk and wine.
Stir over medium heat until boiling.
Add cheese, salt, paprika, mushrooms and onion.
Fold in crabmeat.
Serve on toasted English muffin.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Refrigerate until serving. May top off with a scoop of peach yogurt or Cool Whip, if desired. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake batter by package instructions.
Pour half of the batter into a 9 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese and onion together.
Spoon on rectangle crescents rolls.
Fold 4 corners into middle and pinch. Bake according to time and temperature on rolls package.
Heat cream of chicken soup and spoon over top of baked chicken rolls.

title: letter or number pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar; let stand 5 minutes, then stir in flour and salt. Knead on floured board and divide into 12 pieces.
Roll each piece into 10-inch rope and shape into a letter or number.
Place on greased baking sheet; brush with the egg-water mixture and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 13 minutes.
Yields 12 pieces.

title: icing
directions: Cook flour and milk to a paste; let cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add paste to cream mixture.
Beat at high speed, then add vanilla.

title: peanut butter fudge(no cook)
directions: Mix margarine, syrup, peanut butter, salt, vanilla and nuts in a big bowl. Add sugar gradually.
Pour out on board and knead well. Roll out about 1/2-inch thick and cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds of fudge.

title: dump cake
directions: Place layer of pineapple with juice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan, then a layer of cherry pie filling, spreading evenly. Add layer of dry cake mix, smoothing lightly with a fork. Sprinkle on nuts.
Cut margarine into pats and place evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: congealed cola salad
directions: Heat cola and dissolve Jell-O.
Pour in pineapple, nuts and cream cheese.
Mix by hand and pour into a mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: crunchy ice cream bars
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix egg mixture with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and stir well.
Bake in 2 to 3 greased cake pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan and 1 small cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large casserole dish, 8 x 8-inch, mix cream-style corn, whole kernel corn, egg and butter.
Sprinkle corn meal mix on top.
Do not mix or stir.
Just mash down enough to be moist.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: poulet normandy
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix the next 3 ingredients into the other.
Place 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
This will make a thin layer.
Layer with chopped chicken. Place other half of mixture on top.
Mix 1 1/3 cups milk and 2 eggs; pour these 2 ingredients on top of casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O and cool.
Add strawberries and pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate for 2 hours and top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate covered fantasy
directions: Mix together Teddy Grahams crumbs, sugar and butter.
Pat into an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been lined with tinfoil and place in refrigerator to set.

In a large bowl, mix Cool Whip, vanilla pudding, grated chocolate and add nut topping last; blend well. Take crumb layer from fridge and add layer of caramel topping. Add Cool Whip mixture on top of caramel.
Cover with tinfoil and place in freezer at least 2 hours.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, water, cocoa, soda and vanilla together.
Add mayonnaise.
Add flour; beat well.
Grease and flour bottom of pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 45 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hidden jam muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, combine evaporated milk, water, shortening and egg.
Add liquid mixture to flour mixture and mix just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling one-third full.
Drop about 1 teaspoon jam into center of each muffin.
Spoon remaining batter over jam, filling each tin two-thirds full.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over muffins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: cream-style corn
directions: Cut and scrape corn cobs.
Add flour, sugar, salt, pepper and water.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add corn mixture and stir constantly.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: seafood crepes
directions: Cook mushrooms and 3 tablespoons of green onion in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in seafood, cream cheese, half and half and parsley.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cream cheese is melted.
Stir in sherry.

title: tina's cheese ball
directions: Roll in chili powder and pecans.
Chill for 1 hour in refrigerator and serve on crackers.

title: stay up all night cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 315°.
Beat egg whites to hold stiff points. Gradually add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Fold in chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn off heat.
Leave overnight.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pepperidge farm chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in dish (9 x 13-inch).
Add half of stuffing.
Boil chicken; break up in pieces and put on stuffing.
Mix the soup and sour cream together.
Spread over chicken.
Cover with rest of stuffing.
Pour broth over all.
Bake at 350° until it boils.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: easy salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl, mix well 1/4 cup of the soup, beef, crumbs, egg and onion. Shape firmly into desired number of patties (about 6).
In skillet over medium-high heat, fry patties until browned on both sides. Drain off all drippings.
Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms, if desired. Return patties to skillet. Reduce heat to low. Simmer 20 minutes or until done, turning patties occasionally.

title: jam oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch pan.
In medium bowl, cream butter and brown sugar.
Add extract.
In another medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and oats.
Thoroughly mix together until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Firmly pat remaining mixture into the greased 8-inch pan.
Spread jam, jelly or preserves to within 1/4-inch of edge.
Top with remaining cup of mixture.
Pat down.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until lightly golden.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: sloppy joes(50 servings)
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add other ingredients and cook until well blended for good flavor, at least one hour.

title: cheese cake in the sky
directions: Butter and flour a 12 x 4-inch spring-form pan.

title: shrimp spirals
directions: Combine shrimp, cream cheese, pimiento and green onion.
Roll out pastry to a 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread shrimp mixture over half the pastry.
Fold in half over shrimp to a 15 x 5-inch rectangle.
Cut into 15 one-inch wide strips.
Hold each strip at both ends and twist to form a spiral.
Place on ungreased baking pan (press ends down).
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger. Add other ingredients and cook approximately 30 minutes. Add water if too thick.

title: st. patrick's day cake
directions: Mix together and bake in greased and floured angel food pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, heat blackberries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water to boiling.
Meanwhile in a medium bowl, sift flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar.
With a pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor fashion, cut in shortening until it is like coarse crumbs.
With fork, lightly mix in milk to form soft dough.
Drop dough by tablespoon into boiling fruit. Simmer dumplings, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in oil, onion, garlic, salt & pepper.
Chop tomatoes up with potato masher or put in blender.
Add to meat. Add tomato paste and 2 tomato paste cans of water.
Add parsley, basil, pepperoni and mushrooms.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Cook lasagna. Mix cottage cheese with 2 eggs.
Cook in layers:
Lasagna, Meat Mixture, Lasagna, Cottage Cheese, Lasagna, Mozzarella.

title: snicker doodles
directions: Combine all ingredients together mixing well.
Roll into little balls and roll into a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Flatten a little with the bottom of a glass.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: home fries*
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Chill. Slice into 1/2-inch slices. In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove from pan, leaving grease in pan. Add onions to bacon and cook over moderate heat until soft, about 10 minutes. Add potatoes and cook slowly. Add teaspoon of butter, if necessary. Cook until brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dishwasher trout
directions: Place fish in a large piece of heavy aluminum foil.
Add onion, mushrooms, parsley and wine.
Wrap tight to waterproof. Place on top rack of dishwasher.
Turn dishwasher to full cycle. When cycle is complete, fish will be cooked.
Remove from dishwasher and open foil.
Dot fish with butter and sprinkle with seasoning.
Place under broiler until lightly browned.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place vegetables and broth in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are done.
Mix milk, cornstarch, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add to cooked vegetables. Cook, stirring constantly, until soup is lightly thickened and mixture begins to boil. Remove from heat. Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream shortening (or more) and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
In another bowl, combine soup, water and soda.
Sift together in separate bowl the dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and soup alternately to cream mixture.
Mix well and bake in 9 x 13-inch baking pan in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: pasta and fagioli(pasta and beans)
directions: In 2-quart nonstick saucepan, heat oil.
Add leeks and garlic and saute over medium flame until lightly browned, about 2 minutes.
Add carrot and celery and saute until vegetables begin to soften, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Add pinto beans with reserved liquid, basil, oregano and pepper and stir to combine.
Simmer 10 minutes longer to allow flavor to blend.
To serve, spoon 1 cup macaroni into each of 4 individual bowls and top each serving with an equal amount of bean mixture.
Sprinkle each serving with 2 teaspoons cheese just before serving.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Blend all ingredients except zucchini.
Add zucchini last. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Can be made ahead of time.
Also can be frozen.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze overnight.
Thaw slightly, cut and serve.

title: ebleskiver
directions: Beat egg yolks, add sugar, salt and buttermilk, then flour, soda and baking powder which have been sifted together.
Last, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place small amount of oil in each cup of pan (Ebleskiver pan).
Fill 2/3 full of batter.
Cook until bubbly, turn with fork.
Serve with butter, jam, syrup or powdered sugar.

title: candy bake
directions: Mix flour and water in bowl.
Add salt a little at a time to mixture until it is like pie dough.
Food coloring can be added if you want colored clay.

title: pork chop sloppey
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: jami's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven at 425°.
In large bowl combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Mix lightly with apples.
Roll out half of pastry and line 9-inch pie plate.
Place apples in pie crust. Dot with butter.
Fit top crust and flute edges.
Cut 4 vent holes in top crust.
Place pie plate on low baking rack.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Shield edge of crust with a strip of aluminum foil 10 to 15 minutes before pie finishes baking.

title: better-than-sex cake #2
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, bake cake according to package directions. Meanwhile, in medium saucepan, combine pineapple with its juice and sugar; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick and syrupy, about 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs; mash bananas thoroughly. Add butter. Add sifted flour and sugar to mixture. Add vanilla and nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350° in 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until squash is tender.
Drain well and mash; set aside.

title: glazed ham loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Mold into 3 large loaves or mold into individual portion size on a cookie sheet.
Bake large loaves for one hour and small loaves for 1/2 hour at 325°.
Remove from oven and glaze with sauce.

title: fruit bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Crushed pineapple works good in it, also. Bake in buttered tube pan in a 350° oven for about 45 to 60 minutes.
Use a little cherry juice to thin batter.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles using package directions.
Drain.
Combine noodles, tuna (drained), mayonnaise, celery, onion, green pepper, canned pimiento and salt.
Blend cream of celery soup and milk; heat through.
Add 1 cup (4 ounces) American cheese, heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole dish.
If desired, top with 1/2 cup toasted, slivered almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook the fresh or frozen carrots until tender.
Cook just until tender and not soft.
In separate saucepan, mix the soup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Heat until well mixed and sugar dissolves.
Add the Chef's seasoning, chopped bell pepper or 1 cup frozen peppers.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight. Is good up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: peanut rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a covered 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown ground pork in skillet with onion.
Scramble eggs on side; then add to pork and onion.
Stir in about 2 tablespoons of soy sauce.
Keep warm on low heat.
Bring a pot of water to a boil, when boiling, add shredded cabbage and carrots.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes (no more); then drain water.
Add cabbage and carrots to pork mixture.
Let simmer.
Place wrapper on flat surface.
Add about 1 or 2 tablespoons of mixture in center of wrapper.
Fold and deep fry.

title: yellow angel cake
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add water and beat until thick.
Add sugar, gradually, beating constantly (10 minutes at high speed).
Fold in flavoring.
Sift flour and salt together 3 times.
Carefully fold into egg yolk mixture.

title: cheesy baked potatoes
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 1 hour.

title: chicken tomato tenders(microwave)
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper
and paprika on chicken; place in browning bag.
Add
1/2 can water, bay leaves, diced tomatoes, onion, parsley and
oregano.
Cook in microwave for 16 minutes on High or until done.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel, devein and wash shrimp.
Saute onion in oil (about 6 to 8 minutes).
Stir in garlic and green pepper.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Blend in flour; add tomato sauce and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in water, thyme, parsley, shrimp, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Cook all ingredients in skillet, add according to taste.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Pour 1/2 peanuts in pan. Melt chips, butter and milk together. Cool slightly. Gently stir in marshmallows. Pour into pan over peanuts. Sprinkle with remaining peanuts. Cool completely before cutting.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken; cool and debone.
Combine soups, broth, spices and Tabasco; blend well.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add to soup. Mix in diced chicken.
Cut tortillas into fourths.
Line bottom of a 3-quart baking dish with tortillas.
Spread on chicken mixture. Layer with tortillas and cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country cottage bake
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese.
Add cottage cheese and celery. Fry and drain turkey sausage links.
Spoon into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Arrange sausage on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Beat in egg.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Fold in rhubarb.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix sugar and cinnamon together; sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until browned.

title: jello salad(tastes like potato salad)
directions: Mix the cream cheese with the mayonnaise.
Chop the cucumber, onion, celery and hard-boiled eggs.
Mix all together; add salt to taste and add to jello, dissolved in 1/2 cup boiling water (no more).
Pour into mold.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix and top with 1 cup mayonnaise.
Garnish with grated cheese.
Let sit overnight.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Peel peaches; remove pits and knife chop finely.
Cut oranges and lemons in quarters and remove seeds.
Put through coarse blade of food chopper.
(Should be 3 quarts of peaches and 6 cups of oranges and lemons.)
Place peaches and ground fruit in large pan and add sugar and spice.
Over moderate heat, bring slowly to a boil, stirring often.
Boil gently for 45 minutes, stirring often, until fruit is translucent and the mixture sheets from a metal spoon.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam and put in jars at once. Makes 20 (8 ounce) jars.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and about 3 cups flour.
Beat thoroughly about 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil. Gradually add rest of flour until correct consistency.
Mix by hand until smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover with damp towel or plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator (can be stored 3 to 5 days).
Shape in rolls.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes depending on size of rolls.

title: roy's mom's fried chicken
directions: Wash cut up chicken. Drain. Salt chicken.
Beat eggs and place in bowl.
Pour 1 1/2 cups flour in separate bowl.
Place grease in black iron skillet.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then dip in flour.
Place in skillet. Cover with aluminum foil and cook 20 minutes.
Turn and brown on other side. Total cook time is approximately 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Reserve enough sour cream, chili, tomatoes, cheese and Doritos to garnish top of the salad.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar with butter.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Put 2 cups or more of fruit on top of batter.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar on top and pour 1 cup boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Stirring occasionally, brown ground beef in a medium skillet over medium-high heat.
Remove from heat; drain.
Stir in salsa and taco seasoning.
In a medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, one cup Cheddar cheese and eggs.

Grease two 8-inch square baking pans. Place 4 tortillas over bottom and up sides of each pan. Spoon 1/4 of meat mixture and 1/4 of cottage cheese mixture over tortillas in each pan. Place 1 tortilla in center of each pan. Spoon remaining 1/4 of meat mixture and remaining 1/4 of cottage cheese mixture over tortilla in each pan.
Sprinkle with green chiles, olives and remaining 1 cup Cheddar cheese; cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until heated through.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve warm.

title: hazel's soda cracker bar(heath bar)
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
Place 1 layer of soda crackers on foil (about 40 squares or 1 tube).
Mix brown sugar and butter (not oleo).
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Spread even.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until the crackers float.
Place chocolate chips on top of crackers. When soft, spread thin.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Combine Jello, sugar and water in sauce pan.
Bring to a boil to dissolve.
Remove from heat and stir in pineapple and baby food. Set aside to cool.

title: a pie "easy as pie"
directions: Put oven at 350°.
Let heat and put stick of butter in pan in oven and melt butter.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour mixture over butter, then pour fruit in.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: good breakfast
directions: Grease pan.
Place 6 slices of bread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (fill all spaces).
Spread grated cheese, celery, green pepper and/or onions.
Spread bacon, ham or shrimp.
Top with remaining bread.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over bread.
Make sure it is all wet and covered.
(Can top with tomato slices, if desired; I didn't.)
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes and serve.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie crusts.
Bake in 350° oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 2 pies.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips together, then remove from heat.
Add cereal making sure entirely covered by mixture. Put the powdered sugar in a paper bag.
Add coated cereal and shake well.
Let cool.

title: geeso(from native paraguay)
directions: In a pot, saut onions and peppers in vegetable oil until soft. Add stew meat, cook until brown.
Add tomato juice, bone, salt, and 1 c. water.
Turn to low heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add 6 c. hot water and noodles, boil 5 - 7 min.
For a quick meal, meat may be cooked 1 day ahead of time.

title: chinese fudge
directions: Heat the evaporated milk to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add in the sugar, butter and cocoa.
Return to heat and stir until butter is melted.
Stir in peanut butter until well blended.
Drop in the vanilla and cut in the rolled oats.
Place in greased pan.
Cut into cubes while still warm.

title: spiced roast beef
directions: Place eye roast in large ovenproof plastic baking bag.
Place bag in a shallow roasting pan, large enough to hold it comfortably.
Mix all of the other ingredients together and pour over roast beef.
Seal the bag and puncture the top in several places with a knife.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours. Remove from oven and let meat cool slightly.
Cut open the bag and remove meat. Pour sauce in a bowl, discarding the bay leaves. Sauce is great served over the meat.

title: mexican appetizers
directions: Ingredients are fixed and put on as layers.
Layer one is can of refried beans and sour cream.
Put on large dinner plate. Layer 2 is mayonnaise and taco mix.
Layer 3 is onion, tomatoes and olives.
Place grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Is best if made ahead about 10 to 24 hours.
Serve with taco chips.

title: low-fat strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in bottom of a 10-inch pie pan.
Add pudding mix with 2 cups of cold water; then boil until it becomes thickened.
Add dry jello.
Pour over strawberries.
Chill until set.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Make cake as directed.
Cool, so you can cut it in thirds. Divide the strawberries in thirds.
Do the same with the cream, then layer these.

title: apricot salad
directions: Beat baby food and cream cheese until smooth.

title: really good icing
directions: Mix cold milk and cornstarch together until cornstarch dissolves.
Heat mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly or until your arm becomes paralyzed.
Suddenly the mixture will be come thick like custard.
Stir a few more times.
Allow mixture to cool completely.
Can put mixture in refrigerator to cool quicker.

title: crisscross peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening.
Cream well.
Add eggs, well beaten, vanilla, the flour sifted with the salt and soda, then the peanut butter.
Mix well and knead.
Roll into balls about 1/4-inch across.
Place 1 inch apart on greased pan.
Press with fork lengthwise and then crosswise.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes. Makes about 15 dozen cookies, 1 1/2 inches in diameter.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine buttermilk and soda. Blend flour and shortening with pastry blender.
Add sugar to flour mixture.
Mix yeast, water, buttermilk and soda; add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Place in airtight container in refrigerator.
Keeps for several days.

title: sausage cheese grits casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 3-quart baking dish.

title: sloppy joes for a crowd
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine hamburger with rest of ingredients and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Yields approximately 90 sandwiches.

title: quick chicken spaghetti
directions: Add 1 cup of broth to water, cook spaghetti, drain.
Mix chicken, soups and	onion, add to spaghetti.
Add some cubes of velveeta, add more broth if needed.
Put mixture in a baking dish, top with velveeta.	Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
May add rum, if desired.

title: harvest fruit punch
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over the tea.
Steep for 5 minutes and then strain.
Dissolve sugar in warm tea.
Add fruit juices and 2 quarts of boiling water.
Garnish with fruit slices.
Serve while hot.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: In
quart casserole, combine apples, cranberries and sugar; top
with
mixture
of remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1
hour
or
until bubbly and lightly browned. Serve hot. Good with chicken or turkey.
Serves 8.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cube the meat.
Wash the peppers; remove the seeds and core. Then dice.
Heat Mazola in a medium frying pan; add the Karo and brown the meat and peppers in it, cooking about 7 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch and seasonings; gradually add the stock.
Boil 3 minutes and serve over rice.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Grease a tube or Bundt pan and pour in mixed ingredients, except sugar.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes before turning pan over.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, eggs, vanilla and sugar until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon bread
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
When done, pour juice of 1 lemon and 1/3 cup sugar mixed together over hot bread.
Leave in pan.

title: twice baked sweet potatoes
directions: Cut each potato in 1/2 lengthwise.
Scoop out centers, leaving 1/2 inch shell.
Mash potatoes.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Mix until smooth.
Gradually add pineapple; beat until fluffy.
Stir in 2 cups marshmallows and nuts.
Spoon into shells.
Toss together remaining margarine, marshmallows and nuts.
Sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: ozark bakeless pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, nuts and pineapple.
Crush the graham crackers and in a dish place a thick layer of crackers.
Then place the mixture and top with remainder of crackers.
Let set for 12 hours in refrigerator and serve with whipped cream.

title: pickles
directions: Pour off juice from pickles.
Slice or cut into chunks and return to jar.
Heat until hot the sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour over pickles.
Shake.
Let stand for 24 hours.

title: microwave dill cabbage wedges(lo-fat)
directions: Snap off any tough outer leaves from the cabbage and slice off stem.
Cut cabbage in half through its core, then slice each half into quarters, making 8 wedges.
Arrange wedges in two concentric circles in a 9-inch glass pie plate.
(Dish will be mostly full.) Sprinkle with onion, carrot and dill.
Pour on stock. Cover plate with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High 6 minutes. Rotate dish a half turn and microwave another 6 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Let stand, covered, about 5 minutes to finish cooking. Drain.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yum yum banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together. Add eggs, flour and baking soda. Stir in remaining ingredients. Grease and flour pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out dry.

title: baked chow mein
directions: Brown meat and vegetables.
Drain well to remove all fat.
Add water, soups and soy sauce to rice.
Add browned, drained meat and vegetables.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at least 1 hour at 325°.
Cover the top with noodles and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Sprinkle canning salt on cucumbers, onions and peppers and let stand 1 hour, then drain (very little liquid).
Stir sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed until dissolved.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Add 20 Ritz crackers, boil 1 1/2 minutes more.
Remove from heat-add chunk of butter and cinnamon.
Cool.
Put in a regular 8-inch pie crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream butter and 10x sugar.
Crumble in flour and salt. Line 8 x
8-inch
pan
and
bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Mix together
eggs,
sugar,
flour and lemon juice.
Pour over hot crust
and	bake
to
minutes.
Cut in squares and sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Do not use metal spoon.
Put starter in refrigerator 3 to 5 days and take out and feed with 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons instant mashed potatoes and 1 cup warm water.
Let starter stay out of refrigerator 1 day (8 to 12 hours).
It will be real bubbly.
Take 1 cup out for bread and refrigerate remaining starter.
Feed again in 3 to 5 days.
If not making bread, throw away 1 cup or feed 3 times as directed before using.
Always keep 1 cup of starter in refrigerator.
Do not cover tightly.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream first 3 ingredients together; add flour.
Mix well.
Stir in the pecans and potato chips. Drop by teaspoon on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients in food processor or grinder.
Add chopped nuts.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into pan.
Add milk and pour into pan. Pour drained fruit over mixture.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 cup water; pour over fruit.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 10 minutes.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Spread topping over casserole, leaving the center open.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable soup with cheese
directions: Peel and cube veggies and bring to boil in water.
Cook until tender.
(Do not drain.)
Make mix with butter and flour.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Combine with veggies, water and creamed corn.
Serve hot.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, eggs, salt, pepper and enough flour to bind.
Drop by rounded tablespoons in hot butter.
Fry 5 minutes on each side over medium heat until brown.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn creole
directions: Saute onion, garlic and bell pepper in bacon fat. Add beaten egg with milk and corn meal. Season to taste. Stir mixture until thickened over medium heat. Pour in buttered casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Top with buttered bread crumbs.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown beef in a skillet over medium heat. Drain. Add bell pepper and onion and cook until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir in tomato sauce and remaining ingredients. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: 9 bean soup
directions: Sort and rinse beans, place in a large pot and cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat and simmer gently for 2 minutes.
Remove pot from heat and let stand, covered, for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse beans; return to pot and add 2 quarts water, ham, onion and garlic.
Cover, bring to boil and simmer 1 1/2 hours, or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Brown turkey.
Drain off fat.
Spray 12-inch pizza pan with Pam.
Combine flour, oregano, pepper, egg whites and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter into pan to cover bottom.
Arrange topping of meat, mushrooms, onions and green pepper.
Drizzle on pizza sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt; add sugar.
Cream shortening or oleo and peanut butter.
Add egg, milk and vanilla. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture gradually.
Mix well; shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Place in miniature muffin tin that's been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove and place peanut butter cups on top, pushing down so sides crack and come up around Reese's.
Return to oven and bake 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add pumpkin and spices.
Serve with gingersnaps, vanilla wafers or graham crackers.

title: eggnog bread
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Combine eggnog, egg and butter.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Stir in nuts and fruit.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Turn out of pan onto wire rack to cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hamburger and rice dish
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Add hamburger. Brown hamburger.
Add water; bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover.
Cook approximately 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; cook 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: deep dish tuna pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion and potato in water about 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain off liquid. Stir in soup, milk, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, dill weed and pepper.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Stir in frozen vegetables and tuna. Put into a 2-quart casserole.
Make a pie crust the size of the baking dish, 1/8-inch thick.
Put over top.
Make a slit in crust. Brush with beaten egg.
Flute crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: instant special tea
directions: Mix well.
Serve by putting 2 heaping teaspoons in a cup of hot water.
Stir until dissolved.

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
(May use food processor.) Serve with crackers or bread.

title: robust pepper salad
directions: In a large bowl combine the cauliflower, broccoli, peppers, onion, and cheddar cheese. Add Salad dressing and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least four hours. Serve with slotted spoon. Yields 20 servings.

title: hot instant mix
directions: Mix together well and store in container with tight fitting lid.
To serve, stir 1/3 cup mixture in a mug of boiling water. Wonderful for warming up after playing outside on a cold winter's day!

title: honey chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter.
Stir in honey, curry, mustard and salt; set aside.
Brown chicken in frying pan with a little oil; drain oil.
Put chicken in casserole and pour mixture over it.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese, onions and garlic; spread on bread halves.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Wrap each half in foil.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Unwrap and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until puffed, but not brown.
Cut into slices.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: divinity
directions: *Can use miniature marshmallows, 10 miniature marshmallows = 6 large.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and half of the flour.
Add egg and beat.
Add rest of flour.
Place in a well oiled bowl and place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally. Use as needed.
Form into desired roll shapes and bake in moderate oven until lightly browned.

title: strawberry pie
directions: To the strawberry Jell-O, add boiling water; mix until dissolved.
Add thawed berries and juice.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream.
This came from Women's Association luncheons.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix milk, Velveeta cheese and flour until cheese melts.
Put cooked macaroni in casserole dish; pour cheese mixture over macaroni and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 340° until bread crumbs are toasted.

title: sweet iced tea
directions: Put sugar and tea bags in a pot of boiling water.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Add water for a gallon.

title: guacamole
directions: In a large bowl mix together all ingredients.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: spanish green beans
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onions and cook until soft. Pour tomatoes over rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 30 minutes.

title: beef stew with vegetables(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Put oil and meat in a large pan.
Cook over medium heat until meat is brown.
Add water and salt.
Turn heat to high and bring to boil.
Cover.
Turn heat to low.
Cook for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and tomato juice.
Turn heat to medium.
Cook 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Put 1 cup of water and 1/3 cup of flour into a pint jar.
Cover and shake well.
Add to stew.
Cook, stirring often until stew thickens.
Should take about 5 minutes.

title: orange sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix together and finish filling freezer with milk.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt, beating well after each addition.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Mixture will be very thick.
Press mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes well.
Cook, with skins on, until fork-tender, about 35 minutes.
Add milk and butter and mash until desired consistency (Sheri likes lumps in hers).
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: rice and pork chop casserole
directions: Brown onion and butter.
Sprinkle rice over onion and butter in a casserole dish.
Heat beef broth with 1 can of water.
Add mushrooms and soy sauce to beef broth.
Pour over rice.
Place browned pork chops on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
